Maybe you can go fishing next week?Joey: Look, there's nothing I can do for him right now, he's still in his sweat pants, that's still Phase One. Y'know? I'll be back for Phase Two, I would never miss Phase Two.Monica: What's Phase Two?
STATUS_zh: 喬伊:(審查它）哦，從去年的三明治獵猴。 （莫妮卡滴三明治）羅斯:(假裝在起居室裡釣魚）哦，蓋勒有一個迷上了！ oh！看起來像一個大的！是的，哦！ oh！ （前後擺動桿）這是人與人之間的經典鬥爭 - （搖擺桿和敲打一盞燈。）有人撞到了一盞燈。（越過並拿起棒）就沒關係。嘿，你們，你知道今年釣魚旅行會怎麼樣？當我爸爸在湖中間讓我出去並給了我，“喬伊，你在做什麼？”東西。我可以說，“好吧，我正在用查斯頓哈斯頓爸爸做電影。你在做什麼？”所有人：偉大的！（錢德勒從他的臥室裡進入，所有鬱悶，穿著汗水褲，帶小雞和鴨子在拖曳。）Chandler：你不必停下來玩得開心，因為我在這裡。凱西沒有欺騙你們所有人。 （喬伊）嗯，除了你。 （他們擁抱和錢德勒用小雞和鴨子進入浴室。）Monica：嘿，喬伊，我不認為你應該獨自離開錢德勒。我的意思是他與凱西分手的只是兩天。也許你可以下週去釣魚？喬伊：看，我現在沒有什麼能為他做的，他還在他的汗水褲子裡，那就是階段。你知道嗎？我會回到第二階段，我永遠不會錯過第二階段.Monica：什麼是第二階段？

STATUS: Monica: (looking out the peephole) Ohh, she's looking down the hall. Oh! She looked right at me! Oh wait, you can't see people through that little hole, can you? (Goes back to the door.) Hello!Woman: Hello! (Monica screams)Rachel: I'll be right there! (to Ross) Okay, Ross, please come on! I thought we have moved on! I thought we've gotten to a place where we could be happy for each other! I mean was that just me?Ross: All right, I'll do it.Rachel: Oh thank you! Thank you, thank you, thank you! (Monica opens the door.) Emily?Emily: Yes.Rachel: I'm Rachel Green.Emily: Thank goodness.Rachel: There's been a teeny-teeny change in plans. It turns out that I'm not free tonight. So...Emily: Really?! Well, that's just lovely, isn't it? I must've missed your call, even though I didn't leave the flat all day.Rachel: Oh well, no I...Emily: Oh, no-no-no, that's not rude! It's perfectly in keeping with a trip that I've already been run down by one of your wiener carts, and been strip-searched at John F. Kennedy Airport, apparently to you people, I look like someone who's got a balloon full of cocaine stuffed up their bum.
STATUS_zh: 莫妮卡:(看偷看偷看）哦，她看著大廳。哦！她看著我！哦，等等，你看不到那個小洞，能你嗎？ （回到門口。）你好！女人：你好！ （Monica Screams）Rachel：我會在那裡！ （對羅斯）好的，羅斯，請來！我以為我們已經搬了！我以為我們已經到了一個我們彼此開心的地方！我的意思是，這只是我？羅斯：好的，我會做的.rachel：哦謝謝！謝謝你，謝謝你，謝謝你！ （莫妮卡打開了門。）Emily？艾米莉：是的：是的事實證明，我今晚不自由。所以......艾米莉：真的？！嗯，那太可愛了，不是嗎？我一定會錯過你的電話，即使我整天沒有離開公寓。這是完美的，在旅行中，我已經被你的一輛維納推車一中載了，並在約翰F.肯尼迪機場被剝奪了，顯然對你們來說，我看起來像一個裝滿可卡因的氣球的人塞滿了他們的屁股。

STATUS: Monica: Yeah. Run ten blocks, that'll help the smell.(He opens the door to reveal Rachel.)Rachel: Hey-whoa, slow down. (Gets a whiff of him) No, keep moving. (Joey runs off.) Wow!Monica: So? How did it go with Joshua last night?Rachel: Well, I didn't see Joshua last night, but I did punch a girl in the face.Monica: What?Phoebe: Why?Rachel: The whole night was horrible, it was pouring down rain, and when I got there, there was no Rachel Green on the list, but there was a Rachel Greep.Phoebe: Ohh! So, did you get to meet her?Rachel: No, there is no Rachel Greep, but then this other girl overheard us and she was all, "I'm Rachel Greep! I'm Rachel Greep!" and he let her right in.Monica: So you hit her in the face?Rachel: No, she was already in, but then this big bitch behind me tried to steal my umbrella, so I clocked her. Ohhh! I can't believe this, all I wanted was a few hours outside of work to see Joshua, so he can go ahead and start falling in love with me.Phoebe: (going over to comfort her) Aww, Pheebs.Rachel: Honey, that's you're name.Phoebe: That's short for Phoebe?! I thought that was just what we called each other!(Chandler enters from his bedroom.)
STATUS_zh: 莫妮卡：是的。運行十個街區，那將有助於嗅覺。（他打開門來揭示雷切爾。）雷切爾：嘿 - 哇，慢下來。 （給他的湧出）不，繼續移動。 （喬伊跑完了。）哇！莫妮卡：所以？昨晚怎麼樣？雷切爾：嗯，我昨晚沒有看到約書亞，但我在臉上打了一個女孩。什麼？什麼？菲比：為什麼？雷切爾：整晚很可怕，它是傾倒下雨，當我到達那裡時，列表中沒有雷切爾綠色，但有一個rachel gevep.phoebe：哦！所以，你有沒有見到她？雷切爾：不，沒有rachel gevep，但是那個其他女孩無知我們和她全部，“我是rachel grep！我是rachel greep！”他讓她坐在那裡。所以你在臉上打了她？雷切爾：不，她已經進去了，但是我背後的這個大婊子試圖偷走我的傘，所以我把她偷走了。哦！我無法相信這一點，我想要的只是幾個小時外面的工作來看看約書亞，所以他可以繼續愛上我:(越來越安慰她）AWW，Pheebbs.rachel：蜂蜜，那就是你的名字.Phoebe：這對菲比來說是短暫的嗎？！我以為這只是我們互相所說的！（錢德勒從他的臥室裡進入。）

STATUS: Rachel: No, she was already in, but then this big bitch behind me tried to steal my umbrella, so I clocked her. Ohhh! I can't believe this, all I wanted was a few hours outside of work to see Joshua, so he can go ahead and start falling in love with me.Phoebe: (going over to comfort her) Aww, Pheebs.Rachel: Honey, that's you're name.Phoebe: That's short for Phoebe?! I thought that was just what we called each other!(Chandler enters from his bedroom.)Monica: Hey! You're wearing pants!Chandler: That's right! Where are the guys? I'm ready to get drunk and see some strippers.Monica: It's 9:30 in the morning!Chandler: They got a breakfast buffet.(The phone rings and Monica answers it.)Monica: Hello. (Listens) Oh, hey Ross!Chandler: Ooh, let me talk to him!Monica: Oh-oh, my God!Chandler: Well, can I just...Monica: (to Chandler) Shh!! (On phone) Wait, what?
STATUS_zh: 雷切爾：不，她已經進了，但後來我身後的這個大婊子試圖偷我的雨傘，所以我跑了她。哦！我無法相信這一點，我想要的只是幾個小時外面的工作來看看約書亞，所以他可以繼續愛上我:(越來越安慰她）AWW，Pheebbs.rachel：蜂蜜，那就是你的名字.Phoebe：這對菲比來說是短暫的嗎？！我以為這只是我們互相所說的！（錢德勒從他的臥室裡進入。）Monica：嘿！你穿著褲子！錢德勒：那是對的！這些傢伙在哪裡？我準備好喝醉了，看了一些斯特里普拉：這是早上9點30分！錢德勒：他們有自助早餐。（電話戒指和莫妮卡回答它。）Monica：你好。 （聽）哦，嘿嘿！錢德勒：哦，讓我跟他說話！莫妮卡：哦 - 哦，我的上帝！錢德勒：好的，我可以...... Monica :(給Chandler）Shh !! （在電話上）等等，是什麼？

STATUS: Joey: (rushing in) Hey! Joey Tribbiani! I'm here! I'm here!The A.D: Calm down, we got time, we're running a little late.(Just then, Charlton Heston walks out of his dressing room and starts eating a liquorice whip.)Joey: Look at that, Charlton Heston eating a liquorice whip!The A.D: Yeah, we loves 'em. I've never seen him with-(He gets a whiff of Joey and starts smelling around.)Joey: (trying to act like he's not the one that stinks.) Whoa! Yeah, what the hell is that? What smells so bad?The A.D: You.Joey: Y'know, I can see why you think that, but ah, actually, you know who I think it is?The A.D: You?Joey: No-no, it's uh, it's Heston.The A.D: What?
STATUS_zh: 喬伊:(趕緊）嘿！ Joey Tribbiani！我在這！我在這裡！廣告：冷靜下來，我們有時間，我們遲到了。（那麼，Charlton Heston走出他的敷料房間，開始吃甘草鞭子。）Joey：看看，查爾頓哈斯頓吃甘草鞭子！廣告：是的，我們喜歡他們。我從來沒有見過他 - （他得到了一個喬伊的烈火，開始嗅到。）Joey :(試圖表現得像他不是那個臭名。）哇！是的，這到底是怎麼回事？什麼聞到了這麼糟糕？廣告：你知道，我可以看到你為什麼這麼想，但實際上，你知道我認為這是誰？廣告：你？喬伊：沒有，這是呃，這是哈斯頓。廣告：什麼？

STATUS: Rachel: (entering) I can't believe it! He still hasn't called.Phoebe: Who, Josh?Rachel: It's Joshua.Monica: What, he doesn't like Josh?Rachel: No, I don't.Chandler: All right, well I'm gonna put my sweats back on.Phoebe: Oh no! Wait! Wait! Okay, y'know what, you were right, you were right. We really weren't great at being guys, but you know why? Because we're girls.Chandler: Yeah?Phoebe: And do you know what girls are really good at?Chandler: Stripping!Phoebe: No, listening! Sit! Y'know, maybe it would just really, really help if you would just talk.Rachel: Yeah, come on! What's going in on in there? (Pats his chest.)Monica: Yeah. And y'know, if you wanna cry, that's okay too.Chandler: Okay, look, I'm gonna have to ask you all to leave.Monica: Come on! Chandler!Chandler: Look, forget it. We tried, but Phase Three is a lost cause, Okay? Those strippers were insanely hot, and I couldn't picture myself with any of them. (Sits back in disgust.)
STATUS_zh: 雷切爾:(進入）我不敢相信！他仍然沒有叫做：喬什？雷切爾：這是Joshua.monica：什麼，他不喜歡喬什？雷切爾：不，我不。否，我好吧汗水回來了：哦不！等待！等待！好的，你知道什麼，你是對的，你是對的。我們真的不是伙計們，但你知道為什麼？因為我們是女孩。坐！ y'know，也許它真的，如果你只是說話，就會真的有助於.rachel：是的，來吧！那裡發生了什麼？ （拍出他的胸部。）Monica：是的。和你知道，如果你想哭，那沒關係。謝爾勒：好的，看，我要問你們所有人離開.Monica：來吧！錢德勒！錢德勒：看，忘了它。我們嘗試過，但第三階段是丟失的原因，好嗎？那些脫衣舞孃瘋狂很熱，我無法用他們中的任何一個人描繪。 （厭惡地坐回。）

STATUS: Chandler: Please?Joey: I wanted to go to the strip club!Chandler: I know, I know, but you're gonna have plenty of chances. There are literally thousands of women out there just waiting to screw me over.Joey: Yeah, all right. (Ross enters.)Monica: Hey!Ross: Hey!Phoebe: Hey-ooh so, how was Vermont?Ross: Emily is...incredible. I mean there-there are no words to describe it, I mean the whole weekend was like a dream. (Sees Rachel coming back from the bathroom.) Oh! And you! Rach!Rachel: Oh, hey!Ross: Hey! You were so right!Rachel: What?Ross: Uh, what you said, about us being in a place where we could finally be happy for each other.Rachel: Oh, hmm.Ross: I mean, I, I-I admit I-I wasn't quite there. Y'know, I mean the thought of you and that-that Josh guy...Rachel: Joshua.Ross: Joshua...guy at that club, dancing and having a good time, the thought of it kinda...y'know.Rachel: Yeah, I...Ross: But now! I'm there! I'm totally there! I'm-I'm finally where you are!
STATUS_zh: 錢德勒：拜託？喬伊：我想去脫衣舞俱樂部！錢德勒：我知道，我知道，但你會有很多機會。只需等待擰緊我，就有成千上萬的女性.joey：是的，沒事。 （羅斯進入。）莫妮卡：嘿！羅斯：嘿！菲爾貝：嘿 - 哦，佛蒙特如何？羅斯：艾米麗是......令人難以置信的。我的意思是那裡 - 沒有言語來描述它，我的意思是整個週末就像一個夢想。 （看到雷切爾從浴室回來。）哦！和你！ Rach！Rachel：哦，嘿！羅斯：嘿！你是對的！雷切爾：什麼？羅斯：呃，你所說的，關於我們在一個我們最終為彼此開心的地方。在那裡。 y'know，我的意思是想到你和那個 - 喬什尼......雷切爾：約書亞羅斯：約書亞......那個俱樂部的傢伙，跳舞和有一個美好的時光，想到它有點“知道.rachel：是的，我......羅斯：但現在！我在那裡！我完全在那裡！我 - 我終於在哪裡！

STATUS: Monica: Joey let me ask you a question. What does this light switch do?Joey: Ohh, Nothing.Monica: Didn't it drive you crazy to have a switch and not know what it did?Joey: I know what it did! Nothing.Monica: They wouldn't have put it there if it didn't do something! How can you not care?
STATUS_zh: 莫妮卡：喬伊讓我問你一個問題。這是什麼燈開關？喬伊：哦，沒什麼。什麼都沒有。如果它沒有做點什麼，他們就不會把它放在那裡！你怎麼能不關心？

STATUS: Emily: I can't believe you really walk alone here! I mean, you hear such stories about New York.Ross: No, it's really not that bad. I mean, I-I for one, feel perfectly safe.(At that moment two very large men start screaming and running towards Emily and picking her up.)Ross: Help! Help!! Help! Help!!Emily: No, no, no Ross! Ross, these are friends of mine from home. (Introducing them) Liam, Devon, this is Ross.Devon: Hey, mate.Liam: How are ya man?Ross: Oh hey, that was a good one, huh? (Imitating himself) Help! Help!Emily: So how are you? I've been meaning to ring you ever since I arrived but umm, well, I've been rather busy.Devon: Do you realise that we have not seen each other since the night of that U2 concert?Emily: Oh my God. I think you're right.Liam: (puts his arm around her) Well, actually the last time you and I saw each other was that morning.Emily: Oh, Liam. (Ross laughs and takes her back.)Ross: Oh, Liam. So uh, what, were you guys playing soccer or something-or should I call it (In an English accent) football?Devon: We were playing rugby.
STATUS_zh: 艾米莉：我不敢相信你真的獨自走在這裡！我的意思是，你聽到關於紐約的故事。羅斯：不，這真的不是那麼糟糕。我的意思是，我是一個，感到完全安全。（那時那一刻，兩個非常大的男人開始尖叫，朝著艾米莉跑來跑去。）羅斯：幫助！幫助！！幫助！救命!!艾米莉：不，不，沒有羅斯！羅斯，這些是我家的友誼。 （介紹他們）利亞姆，德文，這是羅斯.Devon：嘿，伙計。 （模仿自己）幫助！救命！艾米莉：那你好嗎？自從我到達以後，我一直是響起你的意義，嗯，我一直忙碌。我覺得你是對的.liam :(把手臂放在她身邊）好，實際上你最後一次和我互相看到的那個早晨。默米莉：哦，利亞姆。 （羅斯笑著帶她回來。）羅斯：哦，利亞姆。所以呃，你們踢足球或某事 - 或者我應該打電話給它（在英國口音中）足球嗎？德文郡：我們正在玩橄欖球。

STATUS: Emily: So how are you? I've been meaning to ring you ever since I arrived but umm, well, I've been rather busy.Devon: Do you realise that we have not seen each other since the night of that U2 concert?Emily: Oh my God. I think you're right.Liam: (puts his arm around her) Well, actually the last time you and I saw each other was that morning.Emily: Oh, Liam. (Ross laughs and takes her back.)Ross: Oh, Liam. So uh, what, were you guys playing soccer or something-or should I call it (In an English accent) football?Devon: We were playing rugby.Liam: In fact we're playing a game at the park tomorrow. You're welcome to play too if you want.Emily: (laughs) Ross play rugby? I don't think so.Ross: What's ah, what's so funny about that?
STATUS_zh: 艾米莉：那你好嗎？自從我到達以後，我一直是響起你的意義，嗯，我一直忙碌。我覺得你是對的.liam :(把手臂放在她身邊）好，實際上你最後一次和我互相看到的那個早晨。默米莉：哦，利亞姆。 （羅斯笑著帶她回來。）羅斯：哦，利亞姆。所以呃，你們踢足球或其他東西 - 或者我應該打電話給它（在英國口音中）足球？德文：我們正在玩Rugby.liam：事實上我們明天正在在公園玩遊戲。如果你想要，歡迎來玩。emily :(笑）羅斯玩橄欖球嗎？我不這麼認為：什麼是啊，那是什麼有趣的？

STATUS: Monica: Done?Phoebe: Yep!Rachel: (entering, with Joey) Hey!Joey: Hey! What's up?Monica: This switch thing has been driving me crazy. So I turned it off and checked every outlet. Now, four of them don't work. Which means, one of them has to be controlled by the switch. So, I plugged in things in all four of the outlets that-that make noise, so that way, when I turn it on I just follow the noise and find out which one it is.
STATUS_zh: 莫妮卡：完成了嗎？菲比：YEP！雷切爾:(用喬伊進入）嘿！喬伊：嘿！怎麼了？莫妮卡：這個交換機一直讓我發瘋。所以我把它關閉並檢查了每個插座。現在，其中四個不起作用。哪種方式，其中一個必須由開關控制。所以，我插入了所有四個插座的東西 - 這使得噪音，這樣，當我打開它時，我只是沿著噪音，找出它是哪一個。

STATUS: Ross: (shocked) Hey!Phoebe: (whispering to Ross) Janice.Chandler: Y'know uh, you didn't really have to help me pack.Janice: Ohh, well when you said all you were going to be doing between now and the time you leave is packing, you didn't really leave me much choice. Did you?Chandler: Well, I-I thought I did but, I-I guess I did not!Joey: Hey-hey, what's going on?Chandler: Oh, I'm packing. Y'know I'm-I'm packing 'cause I'm moving to Yemen tomorrow.Joey: Thanks for telling me!(Janice runs into the bedroom.)Chandler: I'm only going to pretend I'm moving to Yemen, it's the only way I can get rid off her.Joey: Ohhhh, good one! And Yemen that actually sounds like a real country.Janice: (leaning in from the bedroom) Chandler! Come on, I'm gonna show how to roll up your underwear and stuff it in your shoes. It's a real space saver.Phoebe: Yeah, I know, I do that 'cause it makes me look taller.Janice: Okay, Chandler, come on!Chandler: (to Janice) Okay. (to Joey) Joey, trade lives with me!Joey: Nope. (To Ross) Man look at this! Ross, I can't believe you said you'd play rugby. I mean look how brutal this is!Ross: Hey, I can handle it! All right?Rachel: Please, Ross, you-you got hurt playing badminton with my dad.Ross: That's 'cause-'cause you're mom's dog kept-kept looking at me.Joey: (pointing to the TV) Okay, Ross, look-look-look-look, look right here. That's called a scrum, okay? It's kinda like a huddle.Ross: And is a hum, kinda like a scruddle?Joey: Ross! (Laughs) They're gonna kill you!
STATUS_zh: 羅斯:(震驚）嘿！菲比:(耳語羅斯）Janice.Chandler：Y'Know Uh，你真的不得不幫我打包.Janice：哦，當你說你們所有人之間都會在介於兩者之間做現在和你離開的時間包裝，你並沒有真正留下我的選擇。你有沒有？錢德勒：好吧，我想我做了，但我覺得我猜我沒有！喬伊：嘿嘿，怎麼了？錢德勒：哦，我包裝。你知道我 - 我打包'因為我明天搬到也門.joey：謝謝你告訴我！（Janice跑到臥室裡。）Chandler：我只是假裝我要搬到了也門，這是我唯一能擺脫她的唯一方式.joey：哦，好的！和也門實際上聽起來像一個真正的國家。janice :(從臥室裡傾斜）錢德勒！來吧，我會展示如何在你的鞋子裡捲起你的內衣。這是一個真正的太空救星：是的，我知道，我知道這一點'因為它讓我看起來更高。janice：好的，錢德勒，來吧！錢德勒:(給Janice）好的。 （對喬伊）喬伊，交易與我生活！喬伊：不。 （羅斯）男人看這個！羅斯，我不敢相信你說你會玩橄欖球。我的意思是看看這是多麼殘酷！羅斯：嘿，我可以處理它！好嗎？雷切爾：拜託，羅斯，你 - 你有爸爸和我的爸爸打羽毛球羅斯，看起來看看看起來，看起來就在這裡。那是一個scrum，好嗎？它有點像一個哈德爾斯。羅斯：而且是一個嗡嗡聲，有點像一個困惑？喬伊：羅斯！ （笑）他們會殺了你！

STATUS_zh: 羅斯:(嗚嗚嗚嗚“）不是真的！Phoebe：她是對的！你必須停下來！羅斯：什麼？不！不，我不會停下來。我是紅色的羅斯！喬伊：老兄，如果你回到那裡，你會死羅斯！羅斯：我不在乎！我不放棄！我堅持完成這個遊戲！艾米莉：好的，好的，如果你堅持這樣做，至少讓我幫你。羅斯：不，上帝不！這不是一個女人的地方。那些傢伙會抓住任何東西。emily：不，這不是我所說的。我只是可能知道一些可能有助於你造成一些痛苦的事情。羅斯：我喜歡那個。默：是的？仔細傾聽，德文隊有一個弱的腳踝吧一個技巧臀部。是的。和呃，和大衛在那邊，我聽說他不穿杯子。ross：是的？我可以用它，搗蛋，沒有杯子，好吧！好的！

STATUS: Ross: Oh no! That-that'll just bring me down! This was great! I mean I-I-I was great! This is a great day! Y'know what? I'm buying everyone coffee. All right? STATUS_zh: 羅斯：哦不！那就是讓我失望！這很棒！我的意思是我 - 我 - 我很棒！這是美好的一天！ y'know什麼？我在買大家咖啡。好的？如果有人只是抓住我的錢包，它就在我的口袋裡.joey：是的，呃，肯定。羅斯：不，不是你。 （艾米麗得到它。）喬伊：呃，看，你的眼睛仍然突然出現一點，我會去一些ice.phoebe：哦，冰！我是冰的心情！ （他們去了喝咖啡和冰留下羅斯和艾米麗的冰。）艾米莉：你真是太棒了。我的大小兩倍哭。我的意思是，我沒有這樣做的是，因為我四個，我用搖滾洗了我父親的保時捷。emily：你真的很喜歡自己嗎？

STATUS: Ticket Counter Attendant: (on the P.A.) This is the final boarding call for Flight 664 to Yemen.Chandler: Well, I-I guess I gotta go.Janice: Oh, my Bing-a-ling. I'll wait for you. Do you even know how long you're going to be gone?Chandler: Well, just until we find an energy source to replace fuel.Janice: Oh. Well, I'll right you everyday. (Reading the address) 15 Yemen Road, Yemen.Chandler: Okay, good-bye. Good-bye.(He gives the agent his ticket and walks onto the jetway. Janice walks over and looks out the window. STATUS_zh: 票務代理人:(在p.a.）這是最終登機呼籲664到也門的航班我會等你的。你甚至知道你要走了多久嗎？錢德勒：好吧，只要我們找到一個能源來取代fuel.janice：哦。好吧，我每天都在吧。 （閱讀地址）15也門路，也門.Chandler：好的，再見。再見。（他給了代理商他的票，走到了捷歌道上。Janice走過走來看看窗外。錢德勒回到了終端，試圖走過janice，但她看到了他。）Janice：Chandler？

STATUS: Monica: What is it hon?Phoebe: I-I can't find anything that I want to eat! Everything I eat makes me nauseous! I'm telling you, being pregnant is no piece of cake-ooh! Cake! (Chandler shrugs, and Phoebe grimaces.) No.Monica: Aww, honey I'm sorry.Phoebe: God! Ooh! What is that smell? It's coming from the bathroom. Ooh! (She goes to the bathroom.)Chandler: Wow! Pregnancy does give you some weird cravings.[Cut to the bathroom, Joey is taking a shower and Phoebe knocks on the door.]Joey: Yeah?Phoebe: It's me. It's Phoebe. STATUS_zh: 莫妮卡：這是什麼？Phoebe：我找不到任何我想吃的東西！我吃的一切都讓我噁心！我在告訴你，懷孕不是一塊蛋糕哦！蛋糕！ （錢德勒聳聳肩，菲比鬼臉。）No.Monica：噢，親愛的，我很抱歉。：上帝！哦！那聞到了什麼？它來自浴室。哦！ （她去洗手間。）錢德勒：哇！懷孕確實給了你一些奇怪的渴望。[切到衛生間，喬伊正在洗澡，菲比敲門。]喬伊：是的？菲比：這是我。這是菲比。聽到這裡有些東西我想吃東西，什麼 - 聞到什麼味道？（喬伊把頭伸出淋浴帷幕。）

STATUS: Rachel: Well, Joshua's coming in tomorrow and since I don't have the guts to ask him out, I'm going to sell him a coat and put this note in the pocket.Chandler: Oh yeah? (He grabs the pad and starts reading it.) Joshua, give me a call sometime, guys like you (Pause) never go out of style-what did you throw away?(Ross and Emily enter.)Chandler: Hi guys!All: Hey!Joey: Hey, what have you guys been up too?Ross: Oh, we went to see a collection of Victorian doorknobs and the Cupert-Hewitt museum.Chandler: Without me?!Emily: My uncle dragged us there. But, it actually it turned out to be really interesting.Ross: Yeah.Emily: They were so ornate and beautiful, I mean look at that! (Shows them a doorknob she has.)Monica: I don't know how museums work in England but, here, you're not supposed to take stuff.Emily: I uh, I got it from the gift shop. They have really lax security there. (Chandler is shocked.) It's a joke. (They all laugh.)Ross: Bye. (They kiss.)Emily: Right, I've got to be off, I'll see ya. Buh-bye then. (She leaves.)Joey: Wow! You guys seem to be having a good time.Ross: Oh yeah, she's-she's amazing. And-and she's so much fun. And! Y'know what? When I'm with her, I'm fun! I even signed up for helicopter classes. I've been prepared for this from the start. We both knew we had two weeks together, and that's it. Y'know.Joey: Hey that's what all my relationships are like.Chandler: Yes, but in Ross's case, they both know in two weeks that's it.(Phoebe enters.)Ross: Pheebs!All: Hey!Ross: (starts rubbing her belly) Hello! Hello!
STATUS_zh: 雷切爾：嗯，約書亞明天來了，既然我沒有膽量要問他，我要把他賣給他一件外套，把這個筆記放在口袋裡.Chandler：哦是的？ （他抓住墊並開始閱讀它。嘿！喬伊：嘿，你們也有什麼呢？羅斯：哦，我們去看了一系列維多利亞菜門把手和Cupert-hewitt博物館。在沒有我？沒有我？！艾米麗但是，它實際上它結果是真的很有趣。ross：是的：他們是如此華麗和美麗，我的意思是看那個！ （向他們展示了她的門把手。他們在那裡真正的寬鬆安全。 （錢德勒很震驚。）這是一個笑話。 （他們都笑了。）羅斯：再見。 （他們親吻。）Emily：對，我必須離開，我會看到你。然後buh-bye。 （她離開了。）喬伊：哇！你們似乎有一個很好的時光。哦，是的，她是驚人的。和 - 她很有趣。和！ y'know什麼？當我和她在一起時，我很有趣！我甚至註冊了直升機課程。 （錢德勒很震驚。）她在兩天后離開，我不必做到這一點。哦但你知道嗎？我從一開始就已經為此做好了準備。我們都知道我們一起度過了兩週，就是這樣。 y'know.joey：嘿，這就是我所有的關係都喜歡的。揉她的肚子）你好！你好！

STATUS: Joshua: (coming in from a changing room) Okay!Rachel: Oh, here's that trench-coat that you wanted.Joshua: Oh great! (He tries on the coat.) Wow! Yeah, it's comfortable.Rachel: Yeah?Joshua: Man, I could really flash somebody in this thing. (He goes to put his hands in his pockets.)Rachel: (stopping him) Oh no-no, no-no, they don't want you to put your hands in the pockets until you are out of the store.Joshua: Why not?!Rachel: Well, that's because of a lot of...(She imitates someone picking their nose and placing the treasure found in the pockets.)Joshua: Y'know, they ruin it for everybody.Rachel: I know!Joshua: Y'know, I wore that cashmere sweater on a date last night.Rachel: Oh?Joshua: Yeah, it was my first date since the uh, since the divorce.Rachel: Well, congratulations, so do you love her?Joshua: No, no, no, she's nice but, y'know, it just it made me realize that I'm just not, I'm just not ready to be dating, y'know?
STATUS_zh: 約書亞:(來自一個變化的房間）好的！雷切爾：哦，這是你想要的壕溝.Joshua：哦！ （他試圖在外套上。）哇！是的，這很舒服。rachel：是的？約書亞：男人，我真的可以在這件事裡閃過某人。 （他去握住他的口袋裡。）雷切爾:(停止他）哦，沒有，沒有，他們不希望你把手放在口袋裡，直到你離開商店.Joshua：為什麼不呢？ ！約書亞：y'know，我昨晚戴著羊絨毛衣。rachel：哦？約書亞：是的，這是我自呃以來的第一個約會，自從疏散.Rachel：祝賀，所以你愛她？約書亞：不，不，不，她很好，但是，y'know，它只是讓我意識到我只是不是，我只是沒有準備好約會，你知道？

STATUS: Joey: Pastrami.Phoebe: Oooh, yeah. You're a genius.(Rachel enters, she has changed clothes.)Rachel: Oh, could somebody give me a hand with this zipper?Joey: Yeah. (He goes over to her.)Rachel: Up!Monica: You changed?Rachel: Yeah, I did. I needed my lucky dress.Monica: And lucky means, more cleavage?
STATUS_zh: 喬伊：Pastrami.phoebe：哦，是的。你是天才。（Rachel進入，她改變了衣服。）雷切爾：哦，有人可以用這個拉鍊給我一隻手嗎？喬伊：是的。 （他越來越過於她。）雷切爾：UP！MONICA：你改變了嗎？Rachel：是的，我做到了。我需要我的幸運服裝..和幸運的意思，更多的乳溝？

STATUS: Rachel: Care for a cherry?Joshua: Oh, no thanks.Rachel: No? Y'know, I can tie one of these into a knot using just my tongue.(She tries to demonstrate this unique ability, but only succeeds in choking on it.)Joshua: You okay? (Rachel walks away, coughing.)Ross: (interrupting Monica and Emily) So we should probably get going soon.Emily: Oh, but the party's only just getting started!Ross: Yeah, but we-we have to be at the Four Seasons for drinks in 15 minutes and then y'know, then The Plaza for dinner.Emily: So why did you plan a party at the same time?Ross: No-no-no, no, umm, actually American surprise parties are-are-are very short. It's usually, "Surprise!" And then, "Oh my God, I'm so surprised-good-bye!"Emily: But Ross, I'm such having a great time! STATUS_zh: 雷切爾：照顧櫻桃？約書亞：哦，不，謝謝.Rachel：沒有？ y'know，我可以只用我的舌頭將其中一個綁入一個結。（她試圖展示這種獨特的能力，但只成功地窒息它。）約書亞：你好嗎？ （雷切爾吞噬了整體，早上沒有像重重吸煙者一樣喧囂。）你好嗎？ （Rachel走開，咳嗽。在15分鐘內喝的季節，然後是y'know，然後是晚餐的廣場。emily：你為​​什麼同時計劃一個派對？羅斯：羅斯：沒有，沒有，嗯，嗯，嗯，美國的驚喜派對是 - 是 - 非常短。這通常是“驚喜！”然後，“哦，我的上帝，我很驚訝 - 再見！”Emily：但羅斯，我這麼愉快！你的妹妹剛剛告訴我，你曾經像少女一樣打扮，抱著美女茶派對。

STATUS: Rachel: Oops, sorry. Listen, we-we have to have a party tonight! Actually, we have to have one in five minutes, so everybody cancel your plans.Chandler: What are you talking about?Joey: Yeah, what' going on?Rachel: We have to have a surprise Bon Voyage party for Emily. But it's actually for Joshua. (Starts handing out party hats.) Look, he said he's not ready to date, so I had to invite him to a party if I wanted to see him outside of work, and now I have the perfect opportunity to seduce him! (Hands Ross a party hat.)Ross: Well, as much as I'd like to meet Josh and warn him, Emily and I aren't going to be here. All right? I mean, she's going to come by first to say good-bye, and then I've got a whole special evening planned. So I'm sorry, no party.Joey: Awwww!
STATUS_zh: 瑞秋：哎呀，對不起。傾聽，我們今晚必須參加派對！實際上，我們必須在五分鐘內有一個，所以每個人都取消你的計劃：你在說什麼但它實際上適用於約書亞。 （開始分發派對帽子。）看，他說他還沒有準備好迄今為止，所以如果我想在工作之外看到他，我不得不邀請他參加派對，現在我有一個完美的機會勾引他！ （手羅斯一位派對帽子。）羅斯：好吧，就像我想見Josh一樣，警告他，艾米莉和我不會在這裡。好的？我的意思是，她將首先要說再見，然後我有一個整個特別的夜晚計劃。所以我很抱歉，沒有派對.joey：awwww！

STATUS: Monica: You changed?Rachel: Yeah, I did. STATUS_zh: 雷切爾：那首歌是什麼？這一天都在我的腦海裡.Chandler：這是從好的主題駝背。rachel：你知道甚至不喜歡骯髒的電影？我的新男友Joshua.joey：是的right.rachel：不，他告訴我。他更喜歡將某些東西留給想像力。是的，他喜歡色情片。（雷切爾開始離開。）Monica：你去哪兒了？Rachel：我要知道他是否真的認為超級典禮太瘦了。 （當她退出時，Phoebe進入。）嘿，Pheebbs！Phoebe：Hey.joey：嘿！

STATUS: Ross: She doesn't know which one of us she wants, me or this Colin guy.Monica: This isn't how it's supposed to go, there can't be another guy.Ross: Well...Monica: Of course there's another guy!! STATUS_zh: 羅斯：她不知道她想要哪一個，她想要，我或者這個科林人。還有另一個人!!這更完美！現在你必須證明你的愛！羅斯：我不是在證明任何事情。好的，我完成了聽你的。如果我沒有讓你談談我的第一名去機場，我從來沒有把拳頭放在牆上！錢德勒：你把拳頭穿過牆壁？羅斯：不，我錯過了並擊中了門。但是，它打開了很難！莫妮卡：你必須去倫敦！羅斯：什麼？莫妮卡：是的，你必須去找她！喬伊：哦，是的，這是有道理的。是的。因為你已經告訴她你愛她，她沒有說回來，然後她打電話給你，告訴你，有另一個人，所以是的，去倫敦會嚇唬她！莫妮卡：當雷切爾與保羅時，你做了什麼？羅斯：我取笑了他的檔案.Monica：你坐下來讓他有她，你根本沒有戰鬥。我對嗎？你想要同樣的事情要與艾米莉發生嗎？羅斯：No.Monica：那麼，那麼為她而戰！去倫敦！我的意思是，這可能是你和艾米莉！ （指向電視。）那，但是更好。只是，去倫敦！羅斯：真的嗎？莫妮卡：來吧！驚訝她！出現在她的門口！不要讓她離開！

STATUS_zh: 羅斯：嘿！艾米麗：我在你走了的時候打包了。我把一些短褲留在你的枕頭下。思考，想想它有多偉大。默：哦，沒有。啊。哦，離開倫敦，我的整個家庭都住在那裡。羅斯：我知道。emily：我的工作！羅斯：好的，你 - 你 - 你會在這裡找工作！我的意思是，我總是聽到呃，他們外國人進來偷了美國工作;這可能是你！艾米莉：是的，但它 - 它 - 這是我的一生 - 你來到英格蘭。羅斯：不，我不能。我會，我真的會，但我的兒子在這裡;我不能離開他。不是 - 你不認為有任何方式嗎？艾米麗：哦，我不這麼認為。我的意思是，如果它進入未來的方式和＃150是不同的，而且我們正在結婚或者我們要結婚了。羅斯：什麼？艾米莉：哦不，不，對我不應該說的結婚。呃，請不要嚇壞我。我不是故意的。好吧，我沒有說;我回來了！羅斯：不，不，不要。我們為什麼不呢？艾米莉：為什麼我們不喜歡什麼？羅斯：結婚。emily：你很生氣！羅斯：沒有！不！我不是！這是 - 它 - 這是完美的！我的意思是它比你只是在這裡搬到這裡，因為它永遠在一起，永遠是我們 - 這就是我想要的。我的意思是，誰是誰說？那是我我們 - 我們不能這樣做嗎？看，嗯，我和卡羅爾一起在我們結婚之前四年了，我從懷孕的女同性戀中離婚了。我的意思是，這對我們來說是有道理的。快點！我的意思是，在我們的第一次約會，我們最終在佛蒙特州度過了整個週末！我的意思是，昨晚我刺耳了！我！這感覺正確。不是嗎？艾米莉：我的父母會真的很生氣。羅斯：那是 - 你在說的嗎？那是嗎？艾米莉：是的。（他們親吻和擁抱。）Emily：是的！羅斯：是的！我們結婚了？！艾米麗：哦，我的上帝！羅斯：是的！艾米莉：我們要結婚了！

She is stunned speechless.)Ross: (turning around.) Umm, uh, I was just telling the guys...Rachel: Yeah, I-I heard. (Pause, everyone looks at each other, waiting for Rachel's reaction.) I think it's great! (Hugs Ross.) Ohh, I'm so happy for you!(Seeing Rachel's apparently okay with this, the rest of the gang jumps up to congratulate Ross and Emily on their pending nuptials.)
STATUS_zh: 瑞秋：是的！你能相信愚蠢的東西真正讓我們的公寓回來了嗎？菲比：這真是太有趣了，如果你在最後一場比賽之後，就沒有人會才能全力以赴..讓我們假裝不是真的。rachel：yeah.phoebe：好的，圍巾完成了。 （這不是一條圍巾，這只是菲比捆綁在一起的一堆紗線。剛剛，羅斯和艾米麗進入他們喬伊和錢德勒的拖把。）羅斯：來吧！快點。來吧。謝爾勒：好的！菲比：嘿！羅斯：嘿！莫妮卡：什麼發生了？喬伊：羅斯有一些大事告訴大家。羅斯：呃，好的，這是呃，艾米莉和我，我們決定呃，結婚。（幫派被震驚了。）Phoebe：什麼？哦，你也懷孕了嗎？知道這有點倉促，但是，呃，它只是對吧，所以......（雷切爾慢慢地走進她的臥室。她是驚呆的話。）羅斯:(轉身。）嗯，呃，我只是告訴我guys ... rachel：是的，ii聽到。 （暫停，每個人都看著對方，等待Rachel的反應。）我覺得這很棒！ （擁抱羅斯。）哦，我對你很開心！（看到雷切爾顯然是這樣的，那麼剩下的伙伴跳起來祝賀羅斯和艾米麗在他們的待婚姻中。）

STATUS: Rachel: We took our apartment back!! (Slams the door shut.)Phoebe: (opening the door) I had nothing to do with it. (Closes the door.) (Opens the door.) STATUS_zh: 雷切爾：我們拿了我們的公寓！ （舍入門塞。）Phoebe :(打開門）我與它無關。 （關閉門。）（打開門。）好的，這是我的想法，但我對此感覺不舒服。（她閉上了門，但錢德勒把他的腳放在了。）錢德勒：我們是轉回，現在！Monica：不，我們不是！我們沒有離開！錢德勒：好吧，你會在某個時候離開，因為你們都有工作，一旦你這樣做，我們就會重新切換！你無能為力地阻止我們！對，喬？喬伊：我不知道。謝爾勒：什麼？喬伊：我不想再搬家！

STATUS: Gunther: You don't need to fill these silences.Chandler: Oh, okay, thanks. STATUS_zh: gunther：你不需要填補這些沉默.Chandler：哦，好的，謝謝。 （他回到沙發和莫妮卡，Joey和Phoebe。）Monica：Chandler，就像你的第四杯咖啡！錢德勒：好吧，我喝了很多咖啡，因為我筋疲力盡因為喬伊開始打鼾！莫妮卡：他在一個不同的房間！他真的很響亮嗎？喬伊:(自豪）哦，你應該在這裡。你必須去一個睡眠診所！喬伊：看，我告訴ya，我不會去任何診所！我沒有問題，你是一個問題！你應該去一個“戒菸是個孩子，讓我獨自一人”診所！錢德勒：他們沒有那些.joey：是的，他們做！戒掉了一個孩子，讓我一個人！在那裡，你剛剛擁有你的第一堂課！莫妮卡：你知道我曾經和這個那個真正輕微的睡眠者一起出去，每當我開始打鼾時，他就會把我滾到......喬伊：哦，是的！莫妮卡：他會把我捲起，我會停止打鼾。去做就對了。

STATUS: Chandler: Because weddings are a great place to meet women, and when I dance, I look like this... (Starts to dancing really, really, really badly. STATUS_zh: 錢德勒：因為婚禮是一個迎接女性的好地方，當我跳舞時，我看起來像這樣......（開始跳舞真的，真的，真的很糟糕。羅斯在他身後進入他並停止。）羅斯：嘿Man.Chandler ：嘿！羅斯：所以，你們從今天開始四周了？錢德勒：沒有什麼。rachel：沒什麼.joey：我是...（看著他的約會書。）免費！羅斯：偉大！因為艾米麗和我在一個月內結婚了！錢德勒，喬伊，羅斯：什麼？！羅斯：是的！雷切爾：在一個月內：羅斯：是的！rachel：你的意思是，你的意思是，你的意思是30天？羅斯：是的

STATUS: Joey: (sleepily) Yeah, she is. Wow! (Falls back asleep, loudly) How you doin'?(Chandler wakes him up, again.)Joey: What?!Chandler: You're coming on to the entire room! STATUS_zh: 喬伊:(睡覺）是的，她是。哇！ （大聲地睡著了）你怎麼樣？（Chandler再次喚醒他。）喬伊：什麼？！錢德勒：你來到整個房間！ （他結束了在她旁邊拿起一堆雜誌，並引起她的注意，他把它們扔掉了。如果我......

STATUS: Rachel: Ross do you realise this is the first time in my life I'm doing something I actually care about. This is the first time in my life I'm doing something that I'm actually good at. STATUS_zh: 雷切爾：羅斯你意識到這是我生命中第一次我正在做我真正關心的事情。這是我生命中的第一次，我正在做一些我實際上擅長的事情。我是說。如果你沒有得到......羅斯：不，嘿，我得到的，好吧，我得到了那個大的時間。而且我很高興你，但我厭倦了與你的應答機建立了關係！好的，我不知道該怎麼做.Rachel：既不是我也不是我！羅斯：這是關於馬克的嗎？雷切爾:(震驚）哦，我的神。還是不是，這不是。

STATUS: Monica: Ohh, this is soo amazing! I can't believe my brother's getting married! And in London! It's so romantic!Joey: (taking apart the invitation) Hey, pretty smart! Tissue paper! STATUS_zh: 莫妮卡：哦，這太棒了！我無法相信我哥哥結婚了！和在倫敦！這是如此浪漫！喬伊:(分開邀請）嘿，非常聰明！衛生紙！你在婚禮上，你必須哭泣，“手帕？” “禁忌，我得到了我的邀請。”菲比：哦看看！這不是可愛的，羅斯讓Ben地址礦！錢德勒:(進入）你好！喬伊：嘿！莫妮卡：嘿！菲比：嘿！嘿，你有沒有收到羅斯的婚禮的邀請？錢德勒:(諷刺）noo.joey：別擔心的人，我攜帶客人。我們會向他展示：我很嫉妒你們都會去！我不敢相信我從來不知道你不能在你的三個三個月飛行！錢德勒：我不知道.Monica：我從來不知道.joey：我知道！ （他們都看著他）我也不知道，但你應該看到你的面孔。rachel :(進入）嘿傢伙！怎麼了？喬伊：heyyy。 （他們都嘗試隱藏他們的邀請。）

STATUS: Rachel: Who's this from?Chandler: Oh, that's Ross's.Rachel: Oh... (opens it and sees it is a pin) Oh my God. He remembered.Phoebe: Remembered what?Rachel: It was like months ago. We were walking by this antique store, and I saw this pin in the window, and I told him that it was just like one my grandmother had when I was a little girl. Oh! I can't believe he remembered!Phoebe: Oh, it's so pretty. This must have cost him a fortune.
STATUS_zh: 雷切爾：誰是來自？錢德勒：哦，那是羅斯的。羅阿什：哦......（打開它並看到它是一個別針）哦，我的上帝。他記得了.Pphoebe：記得什麼？雷切爾：就像幾個月前。我們在這家古董店散步，我在窗戶裡看到這個別針，我告訴他，就像我祖母一樣，當我還是個小女孩時，這就像我的祖母一樣。哦！我不敢相信他想起了！菲比：哦，這太漂亮了。這一定是耗費他的財富。

STATUS: Ross: Hey guys!Chandler: Hey.Joey: Hey!Ross: All right, here's the ring. (Shows Chandler the wedding ring he plans on giving Emily)Chandler: (shocked) Yes! Yes! A thousand times, yes!Ross: So uh, any ideas for the bachelor party yet?Joey: Whoa-whoa-whoa! Before you start handing out wedding rings and planning bachelor parties, don't you have to decide who your best man is gonna be?Chandler: Oh, it's awkward. It's awkward. Look, I-I don't have any brothers; I'll never get to be a best man!Chandler: You can be the best man when I get married.Joey: (pause) I'll never get to be a best man!Ross: (to Chandler) Wait-wait, so, you get to be my best man twice and I never get to be yours at all?Chandler: Oh no-no-no, you-yeah, of course you get to be my best man.Joey: (impatiently tapping Chandler on the shoulder) What about me?! You-you just said I could!Chandler: I'm not even getting married! Okay, this is a question for science fiction writers!
STATUS_zh: 羅斯：嘿傢伙！錢德勒：嘿.joey：嘿！羅斯：好的，這是戒指。 （顯示錢德勒的婚戒他計劃給艾米莉）錢德勒:(震驚）是的！是的！一千次，是的！羅斯：所以呃，沒有任何想法的單身派對？喬伊：哇哇哇哇哇哇哇哇哇哇哇哇哇哇哇在你開始散發婚禮戒指和規劃學士派對之前，你不必決定你最好的男人會是誰？錢德勒：哦，這是尷尬的。這是尷尬的。這是awkward.ross：我已經問過chandler.joey：什麼？！他必須在你的第一個婚禮上做到這一點！羅斯：喬伊，我想你明白了。我的意思是，我 - 我已經認識他了很多.joey：來羅斯！看，我 - 我沒有任何兄弟;我永遠不會成為一個最好的男人！錢德勒：當我結婚時，你可以成為最好的男人.joey :(暫停）我永遠不會成為最好的男人！羅斯:(給Chandler）等待，所以，你一直都是我最好的男人，我永遠不會成為你的人？錢德勒：哦，沒有 - 不，你是 - 是的，你是我最好的男人。（不耐煩地敲打錢德勒肩膀）我呢？！你 - 你剛才說我可以！錢德勒：我甚至沒有結婚！好的，這是一個科幻作家的問題！

STATUS: Phoebe: Hi, guys.Rachel: Hi! Phoebe. STATUS_zh: Phoebe：嗨，Guys.Rachel：嗨！菲比。 （莫妮卡和她試圖搬出菲比的方式。）Monica：嗨Phoebe.Phoebe y'know它只是荷爾蒙，y'know.rachel：不......莫妮卡：荷爾蒙。荷迦克：...荷爾蒙，yeah.phoebe：無論如何，我只是想說謝謝你，它只是，它只是如此甜蜜。 （她要擁抱他們，他們都畏縮，認為Phoebe即將攻擊它們。）Monica：哇，你似乎做得更好。那太棒了。所以如何 - 事情發生了？Phoebe：好。 y'know-no-no，好的，它 - 感覺就像一切都是關於我的最近一切，所以和你在一起？雷切爾：哦，好吧，我們只是談論我不會去羅斯的婚禮。哦！雷切爾：鑑於歷史和所有這些，這可能太難了......

STATUS: Joey: Ugh! I don't know what I'm going to do! I called the company that sent and th-they don't care! Then I called 9-1-1 and they laughed at me, if this isn't an emergency, then what is?Ross: (entering) Hey guys!Chandler: Hey!Joey: Hey...Ross: I just wanted to thank you again for last night, what a great party! And the guys from work had a blast. Y'know, one of them had never been to a bachelor party before. Yeah! And-and another one had never been to a party before, so...Joey: So uh, hey, that uh, that wedding ring, huh? Man, that's nice!Ross: Yeah, right!Joey: I was uh, I was thinking I might want to pick one of those babies up for myself, I might want to get one of those...Ross: That ring? When my grandmother first came to this country, that ring and the clothes on her back were all she had with her.Chandler: So you might say, the ring is irreplaceable? (Gives Joey a little squeeze.)Ross: Oh absolutely! It has been in my family for generations, and every bride who has worn it has had a long and happy life.Chandler: So you might say, it's a magic ring.Joey: (laughs, softly) Yeah, the stripper stole it.Ross: My-my ring? STATUS_zh: 喬伊：呃！我不知道我要做什麼！我打電話給那些發送的公司，他們不在乎！然後我叫9-1-1，他們嘲笑我，如果這不是緊急情況，那麼什麼是？羅斯:(進入）嘿傢伙！錢德勒：嘿！喬伊：嘿......羅斯：我只是想昨晚再次感謝你，是一個很棒的派對！從工作中的人有爆炸。 y'know，其中一個人以前從未去過一個學士派對。是的！而且另一個人以前從未去過派對，所以......喬伊：所以呃，嘿，那呃，那個結婚戒指，呵呵？男人，那很好！羅斯：是的，對。喬伊：我是呃，我想我可能想為自己選擇其中一個嬰兒，我可能想要得到其中一個......羅斯：那個戒指？當我的祖母第一次來到這個國家時，她背上的戒指和她背上的衣服都是她和她所擁有的.Chandler：所以你可能會說，戒指是不可替代的？ （給喬伊有點擠壓。）羅斯：哦絕對！它已經在我的家庭中為世代，每個磨損它的新娘都有很長而幸福的生活。所以你可能會說，這是一個魔術戒指.Joey :(笑，輕柔地）是的，剝離者偷了它。羅斯：我的戒指？我的婚戒？ - 剝離者偷了我的結婚戒指？！ h-how？！這一切怎麼可能發生了？！錢德勒：好吧，我認為這一切都開始了你說，“嘿喬伊，你為什麼不是我最好的男人。”羅斯:(撥電話）一切都好，好吧！我 - 我要打電話給警察！喬伊：老兄，我搞砸了，你不必把我轉身！羅斯：不在你身上！在脫衣舞孃上！喬伊：哦，是的，我已經這樣做了！他們說他們會在解決所有謀殺案之後看它。好吧，好吧，我們會致電送她的公司！

STATUS: Joey: All right, okay, this is great, uh, Chandler, you get behind the desk. And-and when she comes in hopefully, she won't recognise you because, well, why would she? Uh, okay, and then you buzz Ross and I. (to Ross) You be Mr. Gonzalez, and I'll be uh, Mr. Wong.Ross: Diverse.(There's a knock on the door.)The Stripper: Did anybody call for security?Chandler: (to Ross) You be cool. (He opens the door and lets her in as they all turn there backs on her.)The Stripper: Okay, which one of you guys is Gunther Central-Perk? (Sees Joey.) Hey, Joey?Ross: Where's my ring? STATUS_zh: 喬伊：好的，好吧，這是偉大的，呃，錢德勒，你落後了桌子。和 - 當她有希望的時候，她不會認識你，因為好吧，為什麼她呢？呃，好吧，然後你嗡嗡作響和我。（羅斯）你是Gonzalez先生，我會成為呃，Wong.ross先生：多樣化。（門上有一個敲門聲。任何人都要求安全？錢德勒:(羅斯）你很酷。 （他打開了門，讓她在那裡回到她身邊。）脫衣舞孃：好的，你們哪一個人是Commer-Perk？ （看到喬伊）嘿，喬伊？羅斯：我的戒指在哪裡？我死去的祖母的結婚戒指？它在哪裡？它在哪裡？錢德勒：酷，男人的方式。

STATUS_zh: 雷切爾：我仍然沒有知道它是如何知道它的假浪花，何時是假的朗布，你能看到任何嬰兒嗎？莫妮卡：你覺得怎麼樣？菲比：好的，我猜。我的意思是......我不知道，這只是，我想我知道它會很快就會過來。rachel：好吧，不是那麼好的事嗎？你說你厭倦了這一點：我知道。這只是y'know通常，當你完成懷孕的事情時，你知道，那麼你可以做媽媽的事情。我會成為你知道的，坐在我的皮革褲子裡，喝酒龍舌蘭犬：有些媽媽做那個媽媽做的那樣：好的，這是甚至的悲傷。看，我知道，我知道我搞定了什麼，現在只是他們在我身上，就像我知道他們知道他們知道，我的意思是 - 我的意思是，當這些小時，我的意思是，這只是當這些小時就不會容易嬰兒要走了。媽媽：噢，親愛的，但這並不像你什麼都沒有。你會有侄女和侄子，以及一些方式更好.Pphoebe：是的，好吧。rachel：不，真的。真的，Pheebbs，你不會成為擔心拯救大學的人，或者當他們糟糕的時候，你知道或決定將它們放在利他林，當他們只是不會冷靜下來。 y'know？莫妮卡：我的意思是，當他們想逃避家鄉時，你是那個他們的人，以及他們與之交談的人。羅阿赫爾：而且你只是為了涼爽的菲比！Phoebe ：豪爽的菲比姨媽。我很酷！莫妮卡：是的：你知道還有什麼，哦，我的上帝，他們會愛你。再來。莫妮卡：哦，親愛的！ （他們都擁抱。）Phoebe：你是最好的。謝謝。哦！

STATUS: Joey: So! Things can go wrong! You don't know! What if he doesn't make it?!Chandler: He will, Joe.Joey: Yeah, but what if he doesn't? STATUS_zh: 喬伊：所以！事情會出錯！你不知道！如果他沒有成功，怎麼辦？！錢德勒：他會，喬.joey：是的，但如果他沒有呢？他是一隻好鴨子。（隨著那些我們對鴨子的傢伙進入一點點閃回。第一個是喬伊在浴缸裡玩他和他一起玩，然後把他送走。然後，他們在移動後坐在沙發上的錢德勒進入女孩的公寓，以及錢德勒在床上讀書，他看著巴貝特當所有人都是獨木舟，鴨子在一桶水中。然後我們看到羅斯吃了一些穀物和鴨子看著他。他需要一個燈和將鴨子移開桌子。然後它是騙子在女孩的公寓裡脫離浴室的錢德勒，喬伊在娛樂中心揭示他們的迪斯科古比洞，然後錢德勒與他們一起玩捉迷藏，它與鴨子拍打翅膀的各種場景結束了。和傢伙盯著鴨子的紀念距離。）Joey：我很擔心他，你知道嗎？醫生:(來自手術）有人失去了一個戒指？羅斯：哦，我的上帝！謝謝！太感謝了！ （他抓住了戒指，親吻它，然後做了一個雙重意識到它已經去過了。）喬伊：HHH - 鴨子怎麼樣？醫生：他現在正在做，他現在正在休息，但你可以在一點休息bit.joey：哦，很棒！哦，嘿，傾聽羅斯，謝謝你對此非常酷。羅斯：不，沒關係。

Monica：我會在兩分鐘內見到你。好的！（他擊敗了他的盤子並跑到酒窖，莫妮卡即將跟隨他但是被雷切爾攔截了。在那裡說我的名字，我的意思是，我不能假裝不發生我可以嗎？莫妮卡：哦，我不知道。克拉赫：莫妮卡，我該怎麼辦？莫妮卡：只是呃，做正確的事情。 （使用一些呼吸噴霧）rachel：什麼？莫妮卡：腳趾線。擰針。創造性思考！ （試圖離開，但被雷切爾停了下來。）雷切爾：哇，等等，聽，我想我只是談談他認為它意味著什麼：等等。雷切爾，不，他結婚了。已婚！如果你沒有意識到，我無法幫助你。

(They both leave.)(Cut to Chandler's room, he opens the door slowly to see if Joey is there and after seeing that he isn't, ushers Monica into the room, closes the door, and the security bar.)Chandler: Wow, you look...Monica: No time for that!(They both start to frantically rip each other's clothes off, but are interrupted when Joey tries to open the door.)

STATUS: Ross: Rach! Rach!Rachel: (she stops and turns) Hi!Ross: Hi! I think you should go, by yourself, get some distance, clear your head, I think it'd be really good.Ross: Oh, I don't, I don't, I don't know...Rachel: Oh, come on Ross! I think it would be really good for you!Ross: I could, yeah, I can do that.Rachel: Yeah.Ross: I can't, I can't even believe her! Umm, yes, I can do that!Ross: Okay!Rachel: Okay!Ross: Cool!Rachel: All right!Ross: Come on! (They go to the jetway, Ross hands the tickets to the gate agent.) Here.Rachel: Oh, okay, we're going. Yeah.Ross: Ah! Ah! I forgot my jacket!Rachel: Oh, wait-wait-wait...

STATUS: Oh, that sucks! Maybe that's 'cause she's not really gone. Hm, I mean maybe no-one ever really goes. Ever since my mom died, every now and then, I get the feeling that she's like right here, y'know? Oh! And Debbie, my best friend from junior high- got struck by lightning on a miniature golf course- I always get this really strong Debbie vibe whenever I use one of those little yellow pencils, y'know? ...I miss her.
STATUS_zh: 哦，糟透了！也許這就是“因為她並沒有真正消失。嗯，我的意思是也許沒有人真的去。自從我的媽媽去世以來，每一個現在然後，我都會感覺到她在這裡，你知道嗎？哦！和黛比，我最好的朋友來自初級高爾夫球場的閃電 - 我總是在我用其中一個小黃色鉛筆時，我總是得到這個真正強大的黛比的氛圍，你知道？ ...我想她。

STATUS: I was just thinking. When my time comes-  Listen to me! When my time comes, I wanna be buried at sea. I wanna be buried at sea, it looks like fun.
STATUS_zh: 我只是在思考。當我的時間感到傾聽！當我的時間來了，我想被埋在海上。我想被埋在海上，看起來很有趣。

STATUS: Oh, you-you mean your earrings? Hm-m.

STATUS: What? Check it out, Giants-Cowboys. No, it's the pre-game. I'm gonna watch it at the reception.
STATUS_zh: 什麼？看看它，巨人牛仔。不，這是遊戲前。我要在接待處看著它。

STATUS: That little naked guy would be me. Yes, yes, fine, that is my penis. Can we be grown-ups now? Got me.
STATUS_zh: 那個小裸體的傢伙會是我。是的，是的，很好，這是我的陰莖。我們現在可以成長嗎？得到了我。

STATUS: Hey, hey. Yes, I am. As of today, I am officially Joey Tribbiani, actor slash model. You know those posters for the city free clinic? No, but I hear lyme disease is open, so... Thanks.

STATUS: Hey. Ross, did you know Mom and Dad are going to Puerto Rico for Thanksgiving? Yes, they are. The Blymens invited them. No, I just talked to them.

STATUS: No, not even close. Forget Vail, forget seeing my family, forget shoop, shoop, shoop. Thanks, you can just put it on the table. Oh my god, oh, you guys are great.  Thank you. Thank you so much! Wait, wait, Chandler, this is what you're havin' for Thanksgiving dinner? What, what, what is it with you and this holiday?
STATUS_zh: 不，甚至沒有關閉。忘記vail，忘記看到我的家人，忘記shoop，shoop，shoop。謝謝，你可以把它放在桌子上。哦，我的上帝，哦，你們很棒。謝謝你。太感謝了！等等，等待，錢德勒，這就是你為感恩節晚餐所做的？什麼，呢？你和這個假期是什麼？

STATUS: Yeah, right. Get out.  Really? You don't know what that means to me. Nothing. Yeah.
STATUS_zh: 是的，對。出去。真的嗎？你不知道這對我意味著什麼。沒有。是的。

STATUS: I got the tickets! I got the tickets! Five hours from now, shoop, shoop, shoop. Ok, I'm gonna get my stuff.
STATUS_zh: 我有門票！我有門票！距離現在五個小時，Hahoop，Shoop，Shoop。好的，我會得到我的東西。

STATUS: No, I prefer to keep a safe distance from all this merriment. Ok, we all laughed when you did it with the stuffing, but that's not funny anymore.
STATUS_zh: 不，我更願意與所有這個歡樂的距離保持安全的距離。好的，當你用餡料做它時，我們都笑了，但這不再有趣了。

STATUS: Come on, you know, Thanksgiving. Ooh, you got the bigger half. What'd you wish for?
STATUS_zh: 來吧，你知道，感恩節。哦，你得到了更大的一半。你想要什麼？

STATUS: W-wait. What is that? No, no, I don't.
STATUS_zh: w次等待。那是什麼？不，不，我沒有。

STATUS: Guys? There's a somebody I'd like you to meet.  'That' would be Marcel. You wanna say hi? My friend Bethel rescued him from some lab.
STATUS_zh: 伙計們？有一個我想要你見面的人。 “那是”馬塞爾。你想打個招呼嗎？我的朋友伯特爾從一些實驗室中獲救了他。

STATUS: Phoebe, you're on. Okay, hi. Ladies and gentlemen, back by popular demand, Miss Phoebe Buffay. Wooh!

STATUS: Okay, alright, I have a question, then. Um, were you planning on kissing me ever? Sure. Oh, David, I, I think you are a sweeping sorta fella. I mean, you're a sweeper! ...trapped inside a physicist's body. Oh, yeah, oh, I'm sure of it. You should just do it, just sweep and throw me.
STATUS_zh: 好的，好吧，我有一個問題，然後。嗯，你打算吻我嗎？當然。哦，大衛，我，我認為你是一個掃描的口交。我的意思是，你是一個清醒！ ......被困在物理學家身上。哦，是的，哦，我相信它。你應該只是這樣做，只是掃他並扔掉我。

STATUS: Phoebe. Hi. No. Have you seen David? Well, if you see him, tell him to pack his bags. We are going to Minsk.
STATUS_zh: 菲比。你好。不，你看過大衛嗎？好吧，如果你看到他，告訴他包裝他的包。我們要去明斯克。

STATUS: Okay, so on our no-date evening, three of you now have dates. Okay, so I'm gonna be the only one standing there alone when the ball drops? Hey, y'know, this is so not what I needed right now. Oh, it's-it's Marcel. He keeps shutting me out, y'know? He's walking around all the time dragging his hands... What, uh... what juggling thing? No.
STATUS_zh: 好的，所以在我們的沒有日期晚上，你們三個人現在有日期。好的，所以我會成為唯一一個獨自站在那裡的人？嘿，y'know，這不是我現在所需要的。哦，它是 - 它是馬塞爾。他一直把我送去，y'know？他一直走在拖著他的手......什麼，呃......什麼雜耍的東西？不。

STATUS: Hi, Max!  Are you alright? You're going to Minsk.  You belong in Minsk. You can't stay here just 'cause of me. Oh yes, yes, yes you can. Just say, um, 'Phoebe, my work is my life and that's what I have to do right now'. And I say 'your work?! Your work?! How can you say that?!'. And then you say, um, 'it's tearing me apart, but I have no choice. Can't you understand that?'. And I say (Hits him) 'no! No! I can't understand that!'. Ooh, sorry. Um, and, and then you put your arms around me. And then you put your arms around me. (He does so) And, um, and then you tell me that you love me and you'll never forget me. And then you say that it's almost midnight and you have to go because you don't wanna start the new year with me if you can't finish it. (They kiss) I'm gonna miss you. You scientist guy.
STATUS_zh: 嗨，最大！你還好嗎？你要去明斯克。你屬於明斯克。你不能留在這裡只是“我的原因”。哦，是的，是的，是的，你可以。只是說，嗯，“菲比，我的工作是我的生命，這就是我現在要做的事”。我說'你的工作嗎？！你的工作？！你怎麼能這樣說？！'。然後你說，嗯，“它撕裂了我，但我別無選擇。你不能明白嗎？“我說（打他）'不！不！我無法理解！“。哦，對不起。嗯，然後你把手臂放在我身邊。然後你把手放在我身邊。 （他這樣做），嗯，然後你告訴我你愛我，你永遠不會忘記我。然後你說這幾乎是午夜，你必須去，因為如果你無法完成它，你不想開新的一年。 （他們親吻）我會想念你。你科學家傢伙。

STATUS: And then the peacock bit me. (Laughs) Please kiss me at midnight. Ooh. Uh, I don't know how to tell you this, but she's in Monica's bedroom, getting it on with Max, that scientist geek. Ooh, look at that, I did know how to tell you. And the moment of joy is upon us. Y'know, I uh.. just thought I'd throw this out here. I'm no math whiz, but I do believe there are three girls and three guys right here.
STATUS_zh: 然後孔雀咬我。 （笑）請在午夜吻我。哦。呃，我不知道如何告訴你這個，但她在莫妮卡的臥室裡，得到了最大的，科學家怪人。哦，看看，我確實知道如何告訴你。樂趣的那一刻就在我們身上。 y'know，我呃..只是以為我在這里扔掉這一點。我不是數學的傻瓜，但我確實相信這裡有三個女孩和三個人。

STATUS: There y'go, kids. You seen Sandy?

STATUS: Uh, no, no, see, because not...not all guys are going to be a Paolo. What? I-I'm, I'm having a boy? Wha-I'm having, I'm having a boy! (babbling) Huh, am I having a boy?  I'm having a boy! Oh, I'm having a boy!

STATUS: Oh, honey, honey, tell them the story about your patient who thinks things are, like, other things. Y'know? Like, the phone rings and she takes a shower. Oops!Roger: But you tell it really well, sweetie. Thanks. Okay, now go away so we can talk about you. Isn't he great?  I know, I know. So sweet... and so complicated. And for a shrink, he's not too shrinky, y'know? Oh, I don't know, I don't know. I think that's a little weird, y'know? Vinyl.
STATUS_zh: 哦，親愛的，親愛的，告訴他們關於你患者認為事情的患者的故事，就像其他事情一樣。你知道嗎？喜歡，電話戒指，她洗個澡。哎呀！羅傑：但你告訴它真的很好，親愛的。謝謝。好的，現在消失，所以我們可以談談你。他不是很棒嗎？我知道我知道。那麼甜蜜......如此復雜。而且為了縮小，他不太畏縮，y'know？哦，我不知道，我不知道。我認為這是一個有點奇怪的人嗎？乙烯基塑料。

STATUS: That's pretty much it. But you tell it really well, sweetie. Okay. I'll miss you.
STATUS_zh: 這很多。但是你告訴它真的很好，親愛的。好的。我會想念你。

STATUS: Just trying to get comfortable. I can't sleep in my underwear.  I've been thinking. Y'know, about how I'm always seeing girls on top of girls... Y'know what I mean, about how I'm always going out with all these women. And I always figured, when the right one comes along, I'd be able to be a stand-up guy and go the distance, y'know? Now I'm looking at my dad, thinking...
STATUS_zh: 只是想舒服。我無法睡在我的內衣。我一直在想。 y'know，關於我如何總是看到女孩們在女孩身上......你知道我的意思，關於我如何隨時與所有這些女人一起出去。我總是認為，當權利出現時，我能夠成為一個豎立的傢伙，然後去距離，y'know？現在我正在看我的父親，思考......

STATUS: Hey, Kicky. What're you doing? Well, you're gonna. Are they end to end, or tall like pancakes? Hey, you're not him. You're you. When they were all over you to go into your father's pipe-fitting business, did you cave?
STATUS_zh: 嘿，踢。你在做什麼？好吧，你要了。他們結束了結束，還是高大的煎餅？嘿，你不是他。你是你。當他們到處都要進入你父親的擬合業務時，你是洞穴嗎？

STATUS: Hi.Monica Geller: Hi...May I help you? Yeah, uh, Joey said I could use your shower, since, uh, Chandler's in ours? Oh, I'm Ronni. Ronni Rappelano? The mistress? Thanks. Oh, like, uh, five minutes?
STATUS_zh: 嗨。吉隆納：嗨...我可以幫你嗎？是的，呃，喬伊說我可以用你的淋浴，自從，呃，錢德勒在我們的中？哦，我是Ronni。 Ronni Rappelano？情婦？謝謝。哦，喜歡，呃，五分鐘？

STATUS: Ma! What're you doing here? Oww! Big ring!  Hold on, you-you knew? So then how could you I mean, how could you?! Ma, I don't mean to be disrespectful, but... what the hell are you talking about?! I mean, what about you? I'm...happy...for you?
STATUS_zh: 嘛！你在這做什麼？貓頭鷹！大戒指！堅持，你 - 你知道嗎？那麼你怎麼樣你的意思是，你怎麼樣？！馬，我不是故意不尊重，但是......你到底在說什麼？！我的意思是，你呢？我...快樂......為你？

STATUS: Nothing, nothing. It's, I mean, it's nothing, I'm fine. It's my friends. They-they have a liking problem with you. In that, um, they don't. But they don't see all the wonderfulness that I see. They don't see all the good stuff and all the sweet stuff. They just think you're a little... Intense and creepy.
STATUS_zh: 沒事沒事。這是，我的意思是，沒什麼，我很好。這是我的朋友。他們 - 他們對你有一個喜歡的問題。在那，他們沒有。但他們看不到我所看到的所有精彩性。他們看不到所有的好東西和所有甜的東西。他們只是認為你有點......激烈而令人毛骨悚然。

STATUS: Hey. Oh, okay, except I broke up with Roger.
STATUS_zh: 嘿。哦，好的，除了我與羅傑分手。

STATUS: She barely knows me. We just live in the same building. She lent me an egg once. Aw, right. Hey. An egg?
STATUS_zh: 她幾乎不知道我。我們剛住在同一個建築中。她隊給了一個雞蛋一次。噢，對。嘿。一個雞蛋？

STATUS: Do what, do what? No! Phoebes! Don't you remember why you dumped the guy? Well, what are you guys doing tomorrow night?
STATUS_zh: 做什麼，做什麼？不！菲比！難道你還記得你為什麼甩掉這個傢伙嗎？那麼，明天晚上你們在做什麼？

STATUS: You can not do this. Roger wants to take her out tomorrow night. But Phoebe, you can go out with a creepy guy any night of the year. I know I do.

STATUS: Although, I have enjoyed the fact that, uh your shirt's been stickin' outta your zipper ever since you came back from the bathroom. So, do we have the best friends or what?

STATUS: By the way, Chandler. I cut you out of all my pictures. So if you want, I have a bag with just your heads. Oh, are you sure? Really? Because you know, you could make little puppets out of them, and you could use them in your theater of cruelty.

STATUS: Ok, so now we need, um sage branches and the sacramental wine.  Um, that's ok!  Ok. All right. Now we need the semen of a righteous man.  Ok, yeah, ok. Ok, and I have the, uh receipt for my dinner with Nokululu Oon Ah Ah.

STATUS: Sorry. Hi. Sorry Im late. Wheres, wheres Carol? No... No... No. I think I should stay, I think we should both know whats going on. What? What? What?  Okay, I'm gonna play my sperm card one more time. I see. So what do you propose to do?

STATUS: Oooooooooh. Oh, that's nice. Oh, oh. Huh, Ross! Ross? You are. Well, um... We, we, we were just... Wow! What?

STATUS: Well that works out good, because I'm not listening. Oh, I'm sorry, did my back hurt your knife?  Yes. Yes. Monica, you don't get it. I love you too.

STATUS: Goodnight. Oh, no no, I am. Um, no, I uh, I have done it before.  I uh, I don't know, I guess I'm just gonna see, see what happens. Wha, uhh, what? OK, now I'm nervous. STATUS_zh: 聽到20,000人唱歌“你吮吸！”後會很好。什麼，回顧？好吧讓我問你一個問題。我是最終的戰鬥冠軍嗎？嗯，直到我是最終的戰鬥冠軍，我不會停下來。讓我告訴你一個故事。當我出發創建MOSS 865時，你認為它剛剛發生過夜嗎？不可以。有苔蘚1，燒掉了我爸爸的車庫，有苔蘚2只會在1月安排約會，而我從這場戰鬥中學到的那樣，我從那樣學到的其他人，從來沒有讓一個人站在我的人身上脖子。

STATUS: Oh my God! Phoebe look, it's Ross and that girl. Phoebe! Come on Phoebe, look at that! They are not breaking up, look at them. Okay that's, you know what that is? That is a, that is a second date, that's what that is! Look at that, she just put her hand on his thigh... Ohh! Phoebe, this is all your fault! Now he loves her, he's gonna marry her, and this is all your fault. You said she was bald!! Phoebe, we can't, we just can't just let it happen! Okay, we have to do something! We have to break them up! Okay? Just go in there and like, shave her head! You owe me one bald girl!! Yes. Yes.
STATUS_zh: 我的天啊！菲比看，這是羅斯和那個女孩。菲比！來菲比，看看！他們沒有分手，看著他們。那麼，你知道這是什麼嗎？這是一個，那是第二次日期，這就是那個！看那個，她只是把手放在他的大腿上......哦！菲比，這就是你的錯！現在他愛她，他會嫁給她，這就是你的錯。你說她很禿頭！菲比，我們不能，我們不能只是讓它發生！好的，我們必須做點什麼！我們必須打破它們！好的？去那邊，喜歡，剃掉她的頭！你欠我一個禿頭女孩！是的。是的。

STATUS: You're not gonna die an old maid, maybe an old spinster cook. Hey now besides, if worst comes to worst, I'll be your boyfriend. Why is that so funny? Ha-ha-ha. A little to hard. What am I not ah, boyfriend material? Okay, so we've established my name, and hit me. But theoretically y'know, I mean say we weren't friends, say it's a blind date. I show up at your door, and I'm like (in a fake voice) "Hey, nice to meet, ya. Hey, oh-hey."
STATUS_zh: 你不會死一位老女僕，也許是一位古老的旋轉雕刻。嘿現在除了，如果最糟糕的話，我會成為你的男朋友。為什麼這麼有趣？ Ha-Ha-Ha。一點難。我不是啊，男朋友的材料嗎？好的，所以我們已經建立了我的名字，然後打我。但理論上你知道，我的意思是說我們不是朋友，說這是一個盲目約會。我在你的門口出現，我就像（以假的聲音）“嘿，很高興見到，啊。嘿，哦嘿。”

STATUS: Hey, y'know what a really good rainy day game is? I mean naked game. Strip poker, we should totally play strip poker. Come on! When you go away, you-you have to play, it's like a law!
STATUS_zh: 嘿，y'know知道什麼真正的雨天遊戲是什麼？我的意思是裸體遊戲。剝離撲克，我們應該完全播放撲克。快點！當你離開時，你 - 你必須玩，就像法律一樣！

STATUS: Okay, your band is playing at Arnold's, collect three cool points. Which means, I have five, and that means I get Joey's boxers! All right, I'm gonna make more margaritas! I'm just making margaritas. What?! Oh, come on! Monica, please? He is, isn't he? I don't know, I don't know, I mean maybe it's just being here at the beach together or, I don't know. But it's like something...
STATUS_zh: 好的，你的樂隊正在玩阿諾德，收集三個冷點。這意味著，我有五個，這意味著我得到了Joey的拳擊手！好吧，我要做更多的Margaritas！我只是在製作瑪格麗塔。什麼？！哦，來吧！莫妮卡，拜託？他是，不是嗎？我不知道，我不知道，我的意思是也許它只是在海灘一起或者，我不知道。但這就像一些......

STATUS: Ohh!! Okay, all right. Fan out! Fan out! OH YES!!!!! Yeah, well, I couldn't find any cards, so it was either this or Strip Bag Of Old Knitting Stuff.  All right, relax. It's just a shoe. Fine. Gang up on me! I got you all right where I want you. Actually, y'know it's kinda cold, so how about I keep my boxers on, and give you all a peek at the good stuff?
STATUS_zh: 哦!!好的，沒事。扇出！扇出！哦是的！！！！！是的，好吧，我找不到任何牌，所以它是它的，要么是舊針織的東西。好吧，放鬆。這只是一把鞋子。美好的。幫幫我！我把你們所有人都在你身邊。實際上，你知道它有點冷，所以我怎樣才能保持拳擊手，並讓你全部偷看好東西？

STATUS: Whoa, hey! What are doing? Trying to get me drunk? Okay.
STATUS_zh: 哇，嘿！什麼是在做什麼？試圖讓我喝醉嗎？好的。

STATUS: Hey!
STATUS_zh: 嘿！

STATUS: Okay, Fonzy gives you two thumbs up, collect two cool points. Yeah. Okay, come on! Daddy needs a new pair of electromagnetic microscopes for the Prehistoric Forensics Department! Okay. Take Pinky Tuscadero up to Inspiration Point, collect three cool points!! Yeah! Which gives me five, and let's see who is gonna lose their clothes. Ummmm, I think I pick our strip poker sponsor Mr. Joey Tribianni.
STATUS_zh: 好的，Fonzy給你兩個豎起大拇指，收集兩個冷點。是的。好的，來吧！爸爸需要一對新的電磁顯微鏡為史前取證部門！好的。採取小拇指托斯卡雷德羅到靈感點，收集三個酷點!!是的！這給了我五個，讓我們看看誰會失去衣服。嗯，我想我選擇了我們的地帶撲克贊助商Joey Tribianni先生。

STATUS: Oh, no!! No, no! Hey, everybody!
STATUS_zh: 不好了！！不，不！嘿，大家！

STATUS: Hey guys. So, anyone up for a midnight dip in the ocean? Okay, I'll see you in a bit.
STATUS_zh: 大家好。那麼，任何人都在海洋中達到午夜垂耳？好的，我會見到你。

STATUS: Good night. Okey-dokey!
STATUS_zh: 晚安。 okey-dokey！

STATUS: I-I mean I, well I think I can figure it out. I guess y'know I was born, and everyone started lying their asses off! How close?  I don't even know how that would work! I'm not asking! Yeah. Let's see, my had Mom killed herself, and my Dad had run off, and I was living in a Gremlin with a guy named Cindy who talked to his hand.
STATUS_zh: 我 - 我的意思是我，我想我可以弄清楚。我想你知道我出生了，每個人都開始撒謊他們的驢子！多麼近？我甚至不知道這會如何工作！我不是在問！是的。讓我們看看，我的媽媽殺了自己，我的父親已經逃跑了，我生活在一個名叫辛迪的人，他談到他的手。

STATUS: Shoot! We're out of soda. Really?! Sweety, what are you talking about?
STATUS_zh: 射擊！我們脫離了蘇打水。真的？！甜美，你在說什麼？

STATUS: Oh no! No!! My hole!! What?! What?!! What is it?! Yeah, and I'm a little tired from digging the hole. Well, there's really only one thing you can do. You're gonna have to pee on it.
STATUS_zh: 不好了！不！！我的洞!!什麼？！什麼？！！它是什麼？！是的，我挖了洞有點累。好吧，真的只有一件事你可以做到。你要撒尿。

STATUS: They'll never understand! We were two miles from the house. Scared and alone. We didn't think we could make it. And then Joey remembered something.
STATUS_zh: 他們永遠不會明白！我們距離房子有兩英里。害怕和孤單。我們不認為我們可以做到。然後喬伊記得一些東西。

STATUS: What? We took a walk, nothing happened. I can back with nothing all over me. No! Joey, we swore we'd never tell! All right!! All right. I got stung. Stung bad. I couldn't stand. I-I couldn't walk. I was in too much pain.
STATUS_zh: 什麼？我們散步了，沒有發生任何事情。我可以回到我身邊。不！喬伊，我們發誓我們永遠不會說！好的！！好的。我被蜇了。蜇了壞。我無法忍受。我 - 我無法走路。我痛苦過於痛苦。

STATUS: ...fuchsia and mauvvve. Those are the 66 colours of my bedroommmm. (applause) Thank you, thank you. Ohh, and I invite you to count the colours in your bedroom. (Sees that Phoebe Sr. has entered, and to her) Except for you. You go away. Okay, bye. No. But, it's not like we're losing anything. Y'know? It's not like we-we know each other or anything. Or that have anything in common. I-I like pizza! Oh my God, so do I! Wait-wait-wait, wait! Puppies. Cute or ugly?
STATUS_zh: ... Fuchsia和Mauvvve。那些是我床上的66種顏色。 （掌聲）謝謝，謝謝。哦，我邀請你在臥室裡計算顏色。 （看到Phoebe Sr.已經進入和她）除了你。你走開。好的再見。不，但是，它不像我們失去任何東西。你知道嗎？它不像我們 - 我們彼此了解或任何東西。或者有任何共同點。我 - 我喜歡披薩！哦，我的上帝，我也是！等待等待，等待！小狗。可愛還是醜陋？

STATUS: Who's Chip? The guy who took Rachel to the prom? Why is he calling you? Monica, you're so lucky! He's like the most popular guy in school!! I was just leaving. Why? Did you write it? Well ah, actually...
STATUS_zh: 誰的芯片？把rachel帶到舞會的那個人？他為什麼叫你？莫妮卡，你很幸運！他就像學校最受歡迎的傢伙！我只是離開了。為什麼？你寫過它了嗎？嗯，實際上......

STATUS: Hey, the ad alone cost 300 bucks! What kind of profit is that?! And you call yourself an accountant. Oh. What do you do?
STATUS_zh: 嘿，獨自一人花了300美元！那是什麼樣的利潤？！你稱自己為會計師。哦。你做什麼工作？

STATUS: Hey, here's a question; where did you guys get the finest oak East of the Mississippi? I'm reading your ad. Yeah.
STATUS_zh: 嘿，這是一個問題;你們在哪裡得到了密西西比河以東最好的橡木？我正在讀你的廣告。是的。

STATUS: Something to do with numbers? What? You mean the mom you met in Montauk. She was a cat?!
STATUS_zh: 與數字有關？什麼？你的意思是你在蒙特克遇到的媽媽。她是一隻貓？！

STATUS: Hey! Now? Is it okay if I go out with Chip Matthews? What, that little thing at the prom? Come on, that was back in high school! How could that still bother you? Look, you and I went to different high schools... You went to one where you were popular, and you got to ride off Chip's motorcycle, and wear his letterman jacket. I went to one where I wore a band uniform they had to have specially made. It was a project for one of the Home Ec classes.
STATUS_zh: 嘿！現在？如果我和芯片馬修斯出去的話是好的嗎？什麼，舞會的小東西？來吧，那回到高中！怎麼可能仍然打擾你？看，你和我去了不同的高中......你去了一個你流行的地方，你必須騎上芯片的摩托車，穿著他的夾子夾克。我去了一個我穿著樂隊制服的地方，他們必須特別製作。這是一個家庭EC課程的項目。

STATUS: I believe it.
STATUS_zh: 我相信這個。

STATUS: Stop it! Stop it! She keeps squirming, trying to get away! Just like when she was alive. Well, I'm not sure. I mean, I guess until she y'know, gets used to the fact that there's y'know, a new mom. Y'know, I think she's worried that y'know, she's gonna, she's gonna be replaced. Well, that's not gonna happen is it? Noo.  Okay, I have to return a call in the other room. Well, I'm returning a call from a certain mom at the B-E-A-C-H. I just spelled the wrong word.
STATUS_zh: 停下來！停下來！她一直在蠕動，試圖逃脫！就像她活著的時候一樣。好吧，我不確定。我的意思是，我猜直到她知道，習慣於這個事實，這是一個新的媽媽。 y'know，我覺得她擔心你知道，她會被替換。那麼，這不是會發生的嗎？ noo。好的，我必須在另一個房間撥打電話。好吧，我正在從B-E-A-C-H處回到某個媽媽的電話。我剛拼錯了這個詞。

STATUS: Here, we are. The what? No, I think it's cute. So you still in touch with anyone from high school? Oh yeah, I still hang with Simmons and Zana, y'know. I see Spindler a lot. Devane, Kelly, and I run into Goldie from time to time. Steve Brown, Zuchoff, McGwire, J.T., Breadsly.
STATUS_zh: 我們到了。什麼？不，我覺得很可愛。所以你仍然與高中的任何人聯繫？哦，是的，我仍然和西蒙斯和澤納一起，你知道。我看到spindler很多。黛凡，凱莉，我不時遇到了Goldie。斯蒂夫布朗，Zuchoff，McGwire，J.T.，麵包。

STATUS: ...and then Zana, just let one rip!! You know where I work!
STATUS_zh: ...然後澤娜，只讓一個撕裂！你知道我在哪里工作！

STATUS: You could.... say you're sorry to her mom. So honey, what are you gonna do about the little girl?
STATUS_zh: 你可以......說你對她的媽媽很抱歉。所以親愛的，你要對小女孩做什麼？

STATUS: Oh my God! What happened? Well, y'know how I always wanted to go out with Chip Matthews in high school? Well, tonight, I actually went out with Chip Matthews in high school. No, it's okay, not only did I get to go out with Chip Matthews, I got to dump Chip Matthews. I know!
STATUS_zh: 我的天啊！發生了什麼？嗯，你知道我如何總是想在高中用芯片馬修斯出去？好吧，今晚，我實際上在高中和芯片馬修斯出去了。不，沒關係，不僅我要用芯片馬修斯出去，我得轉移到芯片馬修斯。我知道！

STATUS: What? Oh, I know, I never wear fake ones. I just did it so my Mom wouldn't give me grief about me biting them. Oh my God. Wait a minute, I had them put... Oh my God! It's in the quiche! Oh My God! Okay ah, please don't freak out. Umm, but ah, there's a blue fingernail in one of the quiche cups, and there's no way to know which one. Then why are you laughing? What? You bet I'd lose a nail? Frozen lasagnas? You bet that I'd screw up?! So all that stuff about hiring me because I was good was... You promised Dr. Weinburg, you'd never use that phrase. That's right. My Mom doesn't have any faith in me! Oh, that's hilarious! Ha-ha-ha-ha-ha.
STATUS_zh: 什麼？哦，我知道，我從不戴假人。我只是這樣做，所以我的媽媽不會讓我悲傷我咬他們。我的天啊。等一下，我有他們放屁......我的上帝！它在乳房！我的天啊！好吧啊，請不要嚇壞了。嗯，但啊，其中一個乳房杯裡有一個藍色的指甲，沒有辦法知道哪一個。那你為什麼笑？什麼？你打賭我會失去一個釘子？冷凍蘭薩克？你打賭我搞砸了？！所以所有關於僱用我的東西都是因為我很好的是......你答應了Weinburg博士，你永遠不會使用那個短語。這是正確的。我媽媽對我沒有任何信心！哦，那很搞笑！哈哈哈哈哈。

STATUS: Yes. Uh, can't you wait until tomorrow? All right. Unbelievable!! No, no, that was my boss. I have to go. What are you doing? Why? Wait. I wanna show you something. Just a little gag gift somebody gave me. Put your hands together. I'll be back in ten minutes. Knowing you're here, waiting for me I think it's kinda exciting. Oh. Oh great! I'll keep it in my butt with your nose.
STATUS_zh: 是的。呃，你不能等到明天嗎？好的。逆天！！不，不，那是我的老闆。我得走了。你在幹嘛？為什麼？等待。我想告訴你一些東西。只是有人給了我的小噱頭禮物。把手放在一起。我會在十分鐘後回來。知道你在這裡，等著我，我覺得它有點令人興奮。哦。太棒了！我會用鼻子留在屁股上。

STATUS: It just doesn't...feel like we're breaking up. Okay. Thanks. Okay. I'm getting dressed. When I walk outside naked people throw garbage at me. What is it? Ah-ha, you're not the boss of me. Yeah, you are! Ooh, saucy. You are, you're gonna leave me like this? Okay. But if you don't come back soon, there's pretty much nothing I can do about it!
STATUS_zh: 它只是不......覺得我們正在分手。好的。謝謝。好的。我衣著衣服。當我走在裸體的人外，人們扔掉垃圾。它是什麼？ Ah-Ha，你不是我的老闆。是的，你是！哦，薩布西。你是，你要離開我這樣嗎？好的。但如果你不快回來，那麼我幾乎沒有什麼可以做的！

STATUS: I'm really sorry but I may be a little while longer. A couple of hours, I feel awful. I can't!! I'm in my boss's car! Uh-oh, tunnel.
STATUS_zh: 我真的很抱歉，但我可能有一段時間了。幾個小時，我覺得很糟糕。我不能！我在老闆的車裡！ Uh-OH，隧道。

STATUS: Hello, Joanna...(Realises he doesn't know her last name)...'s office. How little?! Look, this isn't funny! You get back here right now! Why not?! What?! Rachel, could I see you for a moment? Okay, here's the situation. The keys to the cuffs are on the back of the door. Could you be a doll and grab them and scoot on over and unlock me? And on a totally different subject, that is a lovely pantsuit. I did break up with her! She just took it really, really well! It did enter my mind! But then something happened that made it, shoot right out. No-no-no-no-no-no-no!! I can't get myself right out of them! You must have me confused with the Amazing Chandler!! Come on, you have to unlock me, she could be gone for hours, and I'm cold, and (Stops and looks up the skirt on a statue behind Joanna's desk.) Never! Fine! I-never borrowed your Walkman. You got it! Here we go! Come on! This is great! Ahhh! No, I just always see guys doing this when they get handcuffs taken off them.  Hello sweet pants! About what?
STATUS_zh: 你好，喬安娜......（意識到他不知道她的姓）......辦公室。多少？！看，這不好笑！你現在回到這裡！為什麼不？！什麼？！雷切爾，我可以看到你一會兒嗎？好的，這是情況。袖口的鑰匙位於門後面。你能成為一個娃娃，抓住他們，腳踏實地解鎖我嗎？在一個完全不同的主題上，這是一個可愛的褲子。我和她分手了！她真的很好，真的很好！它確實進入了我的想法！但是那些發生了一些事情，拍出了它。禁止禁忌禁止 - 否 - 否!!我不能讓自己離開他們！你必須讓我與令人驚嘆的錢德勒混淆！來吧，你必須解鎖我，她可以走幾個小時，而且我很冷，（停下來看看喬安娜的桌子後面的雕像上的裙子。）永遠不會！美好的！我永遠不會藉用你的走人。你說對了！開始了！快點！這很棒！啊！不，我總是看到當他們脫掉手銬時，我總是看到這些人這樣做。你好甜褲子！關於什麼？

STATUS: Hey, look, you're in trouble either way! Okay? If she comes back and sees me locked to this instead of the chair, she's gonna know you were in here. So you might as well just let me go. It still wouldn't be clean. All I want is my freedom. Freedom!
STATUS_zh: 嘿，看，無論如何，你都在麻煩！好的？如果她回來看到我被鎖定給這個而不是椅子，她會知道你在這裡。所以你可能只是讓我走。它仍然不會乾淨。我想要的只是我的自由。自由！

STATUS: Wow! There's a lot I didn't know about vomit. In a minute. Twelve hundred dollars? You think I have $1200? I'm home in the middle of the day, and I got patio furniture in my living room. I guess there's a few things you don't get from book learnin'. How about zero down and zero a month for a long, long time?
STATUS_zh: 哇！有很多我不知道嘔吐物。在一分鐘內。十二百元？你認為我有1200美元嗎？我在一天中間回家，我的客廳裡有露台家具。我想有一些你沒有從書中獲取的東西。零左下和零一個月零長，很長一段時間？

STATUS: Hello. I love you. Two hours, that lasted! I think so.
STATUS_zh: 你好。我愛你。兩個小時，持續！我想是這樣。

STATUS: What?
STATUS_zh: 什麼？

STATUS: Hey. What are you doing? No! You're clogging up the chute that I spent a half-hour unclogging! Oh yeah, of course you don't!
STATUS_zh: 嘿。你在幹嘛？不！你堵塞了我花了半小時的疏通！哦，是的，你當然不是！

STATUS: Wow! And you got a petticure. Your feet are all dressed up. You're gonna do some feet flirtin'!
STATUS_zh: 哇！你有一個襯裙。你的腳都穿著。你要做一些腳佛景！

STATUS: Hey! (laughs) Move in with me. Don't be scared, I-I know it sounds crazy and-and people will say it's too soon, but just-just think, think how great it will be. I know. Well, so, you-you'll get a job here! I mean, I'm always hearing about uh, them foreigners coming in here and stealing American jobs; that could be you! No, I can't. I would, I really would, but my son is here; I can't leave him. Isn't-you don't think there's any way? What? No, no, don't. Why don't we? Get married. No! No! I'm not! It's-it's-it's perfect! I mean it's better than you just-just moving here, 'cause it's us together forever, and that's-that's what I want. Yeah, I know, so what? I mean, who's-who's to say? Does that me we-we can't do it? Look, huh, I was with Carol for four years before we got married and I wound up divorced from a pregnant lesbian. I mean, this, this makes sense for us. Come on! I mean, on our first date we ended up spending the whole weekend in Vermont! I mean, last night I got my ear pierced! Me! This feels right. Doesn't it? Is that-are you saying yes? Is that yes? Yes! We're getting married?! Yes!
STATUS_zh: 嘿！ （笑）和我一起搬進去。不要害怕，我 - 我知道它聽起來很瘋狂，而且人們會說它太快，但只是想想，想想它有多偉大。我知道。好吧，所以，你 - 你會在這裡找工作！我的意思是，我總是聽到呃，他們外國人進來偷了美國工作;這可能是你！不，我不能。我會，我真的會，但我的兒子在這裡;我不能離開他。不是 - 你不認為有任何方式嗎？什麼？不，不，不要。我們為什麼不呢？結婚了。不！不！我不是！這是 - 它 - 這是完美的！我的意思是它比你只是 - 只是在這裡移動，“因為它永遠在一起，這就是我想要的。是的，我知道，那是什麼？我的意思是，誰是誰說？那是我我們 - 我們不能這樣做嗎？看，嗯，我和卡羅爾一起在我們結婚之前四年了，我從懷孕的女同性戀中離婚了。我的意思是，這對我們來說是有道理的。快點！我的意思是，在我們的第一次約會，我們最終在佛蒙特州度過了整個週末！我的意思是，昨晚我刺耳了！我！這感覺正確。不是嗎？那是 - 你在說的嗎？那是嗎？是的！我們要結婚了？！是的！

STATUS: Come on! Come on. Come on. Hey! Uhh, okay, it's uh, Emily and I, we decided to uh, to get married. We, we just decided to uh, to go for it. Umm, uh, I was just telling the guys...
STATUS_zh: 快點！快點。快點。嘿！呃，好的，它是呃，艾米莉和我，我們決定呃，結婚。我們，我們剛剛決定呃，去吧。嗯，呃，我只是告訴這些人......

STATUS: I don't know. I don't want to move again!
STATUS_zh: 我不知道。我不想再搬家了！

STATUS: Oh, you should here me. Look, I told ya, I'm not going to any clinic! I don't have a problem, you're the one with the problem! You should go to a "Quit being a baby and leave me alone" clinic! Yeah, they do! Quit being a baby and leave me alone! There, you've just had your first class! Ohhh, yeah! I gotta do what I gotta do, you gotta do what you gotta do, you just do it.
STATUS_zh: 哦，你應該在這裡我。看，我告訴ya，我不會去任何診所！我沒有問題，你是一個問題！你應該去一個“戒菸是個孩子，讓我獨自一人”診所！是的，他們做了！戒掉了一個孩子，讓我一個人！在那裡，你剛剛有你的第一堂課！哦，是的！我得做我必須做的事情，你必須做你必須做的事情，你只是這樣做。

STATUS: Nothing. In a month? You mean, you mean 30 days?
STATUS_zh: 沒有。在一個月？你的意思是，你的意思是30天？

STATUS: I'm Marjorie. Hi.
STATUS_zh: 我是Marjorie。你好。

STATUS: Ross do you realise this is the first time in my life I'm doing something I actually care about. This is the first time in my life I'm doing something that I'm actually good at. I mean. if you don't get that... Well neither do I! Oh my God.
STATUS_zh: 羅斯你是否意識到這是我生命中的第一次，我正在做一些我真正關心的事情。這是我生命中的第一次，我正在做一些我實際上擅長的事情。我是說。如果你沒有得到......既不是我也不好！我的天啊。

STATUS: Hey, pretty smart! Tissue paper! You're at the wedding, you have to cry, "Handkerchief?" "No-no, I got my invitation." Hey! Don't worry man, I get to bring a guest. We'll show him. I knew that! I sooo didn't know that, but you should see your faces. Heyyy.
STATUS_zh: 嘿，很聰明！衛生紙！你在婚禮上，你必須哭泣，“手帕？” “沒有，我得到了我的邀請。”嘿！不要擔心男人，我會帶一位客人。我們會告訴他。我知道！我也不知道，但你應該看到你的臉。 heyyy。

STATUS: Oooh look! Isn't this adorable, Ross let Ben address mine! Hey! Hey, did you get your invitation to Ross's wedding? I'm so jealous you're all going! I can't believe I never knew that you can't fly in your third trimester!
STATUS_zh: 哦看看！不是這個可愛的，羅斯讓本地址礦！嘿！嘿，你收到了羅斯的婚禮的邀請嗎？我這麼嫉妒你們都會去！我無法相信我從來不知道你不能在你的三個三個月飛行！

STATUS: Who's this from? Oh... Oh my God. He remembered. It was like months ago. We were walking by this antique store, and I saw this pin in the window, and I told him that it was just like one my grandmother had when I was a little girl. Oh! I can't believe he remembered!
STATUS_zh: 誰是誰？哦......哦，我的上帝。他記得。這就像幾個月前。我們在這家古董店散步，我在窗戶裡看到這個別針，我告訴他，就像我祖母一樣，當我還是個小女孩時，這就像我的祖母一樣。哦！我不敢相信他記得！

STATUS: Hey guys! All right, here's the ring. So uh, any ideas for the bachelor party yet? I sort've already asked Chandler. Joey, I figured you'd understand. I mean, I-I've known him a lot longer. Wait-wait, so, you get to be my best man twice and I never get to be yours at all?
STATUS_zh: 大家好！好吧，這是戒指。所以呃，學士派對的任何想法嗎？我已經問過錢德勒。喬伊，我想你明白了。我的意思是，我 - 我已經認識了他了。等待，所以，你一直成為我最好的男人，我根本永遠不會成為你的人？

STATUS: Hi, guys. I-I wanted to apologise if I-y'know seemed a tad edgy yesterday at my shower. Y'know it's just the hormones, y'know. Anyway, I just wanted to say thank you, it was just, it was so sweet. Good. Y'know-no-no, okay, it's-it feels like everything's been about me lately, so what's happening with you? Oh!
STATUS_zh: 嗨，大家好。如果我昨天在我的淋浴時，我想道歉。 y'know它只是荷爾蒙，y'know。無論如何，我只是想說謝謝你，就是這樣，它很甜蜜。好的。 y'know-no-no，好的，它 - 感覺就像一切都是關於我最近的，所以發生了什麼？哦！

STATUS: Hey guys! I just wanted to thank you again for last night, what a great party! And the guys from work had a blast. Y'know, one of them had never been to a bachelor party before. Yeah! And-and another one had never been to a party before, so... Yeah, right! That ring? When my grandmother first came to this country, that ring and the clothes on her back were all she had with her. Oh absolutely! It has been in my family for generations, and every bride who has worn it has had a long and happy life. My-my ring? My-my wedding ring? The-the stripper stole my wedding ring?! H-how?! How could this all happen?! All right-all right, fine! I-I'm gonna call the cops! Not on you! On the stripper! Okay, well, we'll call the company that sent her!
STATUS_zh: 大家好！我只是想再次謝謝你昨晚，這是一個很棒的派對！從工作中的人有爆炸。 y'know，其中一個人以前從未去過一個學士派對。是的！和另一個人以前從未去過派對，所以......是的，對了！那個戒指？當我的祖母第一次來到這個國家時，那個戒指和她背上的衣服都是她和她所擁有的。哦，絕對！它一直在我的家庭，以及每個已經穿著它的新娘都有漫長而幸福的生活。我的戒指？我的婚戒？ - 剝離者偷了我的結婚戒指？！ h-how？！這一切怎麼可能發生了？！沒事，好的！我 - 我要打電話給警察！不在你身上！在汽刀上！好的，好吧，我們會致電送她的公司！

STATUS: You be cool. Way to be cool, man.
STATUS_zh: 你很酷。酷，男人的方式。

STATUS: How do you feel? Some moms do that. Aww, sweetie, but it's not like you're not gonna have anything. You're gonna have nieces and nephews, and some ways that's even better. I mean, you're the one they're gonna come to when they wanna run away from home, and the one they talk to about sex. Yeah. Oh, sweetie!
STATUS_zh: 你感覺如何？有些媽媽做到這一點。哇，親愛的，但這並不像你沒有任何東西。你會有侄女和侄子，以及一些更好的方式。我的意思是，當他們想逃避家鄉時，你就是那個他們會來的人，以及他們對性別交談的那個。是的。哦，親愛的！

STATUS: Oh my God! Thank you! Thank you so much! No, that's all right.
STATUS_zh: 我的天啊！謝謝！太感謝了！不，沒關係。

STATUS: What do you got there? How come the writing is in Spanish?
STATUS_zh: 你到底有什麼？寫作是如何用西班牙語的？

STATUS: Six-hour trip to London. That's a lot of Monica. Condoms, dude! Don't read my condoms!
STATUS_zh: 六小時前往倫敦。這是很多莫妮卡。避孕套，老兄！不要讀我的避孕套！

STATUS: Ohhh, I wanna come over there and give you a hug and wish you luck on your wedding, but I don't-can't get up. Great! Yeah, could you bring me the newspaper? Oh, have a great wedding! Oh, hey, Chandler I wanna hug you too! Oh, and great! You might as well bring me my book, it's on the counter in your apartment.
STATUS_zh: 哦，我想過來，給你一個擁抱，祝你婚禮運氣，但我沒有起床。偉大的！是的，你能給我報紙嗎？哦，有一個偉大的婚禮！哦，嘿，錢德勒我也想擁抱你！哦，很棒！你可能會帶給我我的書，它在你的公寓裡的櫃檯。

STATUS: (laughs) Thank you.
STATUS_zh: （笑）謝謝。

STATUS: All right! Let's do it! Okay, 'cause that's not gonna get annoying. Hey, y'know what? I was wrong.
STATUS_zh: 好的！我們開始做吧！好的，因為那不是會變得煩人。嘿，y'know是什麼？我錯了。

STATUS: Have fun! Oh, I know. What?! Yeah, well, I gotta work, I'm sorry. Because, I can't! Ross, I told you, no. I can't.
STATUS_zh: 玩得開心！哦，我知道。什麼？！是的，好吧，我得的工作，對不起。因為，我不能！羅斯，我告訴過你，沒有。我不能。

STATUS: Hey! Oh.
STATUS_zh: 嘿！哦。

STATUS: ...and that was all before 10 o'clock. The caterer rang and said it was going to be Chicken Kiev instead of Chicken Tarragon. And then the florist phoned to say there aren't any tulips. Oh, and the chilliest has carpel-tunel syndrome. We're not gonna be... Well, up yours too! Oh, that's not what it means? Sorry.
STATUS_zh: ......那就是在10點之前。餐飲者響了，並說這將是雞基輔而不是雞龍蒿。然後花店打電話說沒有任何鬱金香。哦，最含冷的有carpel-tunel綜合症。我們也不會是......好吧，也是你的！哦，這不是它的意思嗎？對不起。

STATUS: He's just jealous. You'll fit right in; all Londoners wear them! They're all tourists.
STATUS_zh: 他只是嫉妒。你會適合;所有倫敦人都穿他們！他們都是遊客。

STATUS: Hey! Check this out? Huh? Yeah. That's the stuff. What do you think? Well, I like it. Here you go. Oh, I embarrass you?
STATUS_zh: 嘿！看一下這個？呵呵？是的。那是東西。你怎麼看？好吧，我喜歡它。幹得好。哦，我難堪了你？

STATUS: Ooh! I thought of a good flaw! Ross pops his gum! Yeah, I know. It drives me crazy. I'll get it. Hello. Hey, Joey! Hey! Ooh! Ooh! I just say someone on the-that looks just like you on the subway. And I was gonna go over and say 'hi!' but then I figured, he doesn't care if he looks like you. Ohh, they're having a great time with their Aunt Phoebe! Aunt Rachel hasn't been helpful at all. So, do you miss me? All right, the seven of us miss you. Y'know, me, Rachel, the birds, the babies... Of course they do! Or I'm just really hungry. Ooh, the pizza guy's here!
STATUS_zh: 哦！我想到了一個良好的缺陷！羅斯彈出他的膠！是的，我知道。它讓我瘋狂。我會得到它的。你好。嘿，喬伊！嘿！哦！哦！我只是說在地鐵上看起來就像你一樣。我要去吧，說'嗨！'但後來我想，他不在乎他是否看起來像你。哦，他們和菲比的姨媽一起度過了美好的時光！阿姨雷切爾根本沒有樂於助人。所以，你想念我嗎？好吧，我們七個人想念你。 y'know，我，雷切爾，鳥兒，嬰兒......當然他們做了！或者我真的很餓。哦，披薩傢伙在這裡！

STATUS: Okay? But-but imagine a lot more lights, okay? And-and y'know fewer bricks, and-and-and flowers, and candles...
STATUS_zh: 好的？但是 - 但想像一下，很多燈，好嗎？和你知道的磚頭，和和花，蠟燭......

STATUS: Oh...yes..is this..umm..Emily's Parents' house. What are you saying?! No! Ooh! Oh my god! Hello. This is Phoebe Buffay. I was wondering, please, if-if it's not too much trouble, please, umm, might I speak to Miss Emily Waltham, please?
STATUS_zh: 哦......是的...... umm ......父母的家。你在說什麼？！不！哦！我的天啊！你好。這是Phoebe Buffay。我想知道，如果 - 如果 - 如果它不是太麻煩，請嗯，我可以說艾米莉沃爾瑟姆小姐嗎？

STATUS: Hello, Waltham Interiors. Who is this? Where did you get this number? Well, if you're one of Ross's best friends, why aren't you here? Oh, am I on the radio? No, I'm bored with you now. I'm going to cut you off.
STATUS_zh: 你好，沃爾瑟姆內飾。這是誰？你在哪裡得到這個號碼？好吧，如果你是羅斯最好的朋友之一，你為什麼不在這裡？哦，我在收音機上嗎？不，我現在對你無聊。我要把你剪掉了。

STATUS: Out loud? So how are you doing?
STATUS_zh: 響亮地？那麼你過得怎麼樣？

STATUS: The guy was hammered, okay? There's no way, you look like Ross's mother.
STATUS_zh: 那傢伙被錘擊，好嗎？沒有辦法，你看起來像羅斯的母親。

STATUS: I was laughing. Well I didn't want everyone to think I was stupid. My mother's driving me crazy, but Ross is getting married. I'm happy. I'm not going to let anything spoil that. Well, thanks, we like him.
STATUS_zh: 我笑了。好吧，我不希望每個人都認為我是愚蠢的。我母親讓我瘋狂，但羅斯正在結婚。我很高興。我不會讓任何破壞的東西。好吧，謝謝，我們喜歡他。

STATUS: Hello. Oh I'm afraid that plane has already pulled away from the gate. I can't do that.
STATUS_zh: 你好。哦，我擔心飛機已經從大門中脫離了。我不能這樣做。

STATUS: Hey, were the hell have you been? I don't want to hear about her!! No! No, we have an emergency. Okay? Rachel's coming to London. No it's not great. No, she's coming to tell Ross that she loves him. I KNOW THAT!!! You have to stop her!! She's going to ruin the wedding!!
STATUS_zh: 嘿，你到底了嗎？我不想听到她！不！不，我們有緊急情況。好的？雷切爾來到倫敦。不，這並不偉大。不，她來告訴她愛他的羅斯。我知道！！！你必須阻止她!!她會毀了婚禮！

STATUS: ...And so then I realised. All this stuff I had been doing. proposing to Joshua, lying to Ross about why I couldn't come to the wedding. Was all just a way of... Ehh, pardon me? But he has to know how I feel!
STATUS_zh: ......所以我意識到了。我一直在做的這件事。向約書亞提出，躺著羅斯為什麼不能來婚禮。只是一種方式......呃，請原諒我？但他必須知道我的感受！

STATUS: Do something..... Something.... Hey. Have you seen Monica?  (With a confused look on his face.) What?
STATUS_zh: 做點什麼......嘿。你見過莫妮卡嗎？ （他的臉上有一個困惑的外觀。）是什麼？

STATUS: What was all that about?
STATUS_zh: 這一切是什麼？

STATUS: Hey, Felicity. Yeah. Fuggetaboutit. How you doin? Oh, yeah.
STATUS_zh: 嘿，幸福。是的。 Fuggetaboutit。你好嗎？哦耶。

STATUS: (Smiling.) Ohh great!! (Putting the phone to his ear.) Hello. (He begins to escort her down the aisle.) No, but it's okay. She just came in and gave him a hug, that it. No. Ah, I'm-I'm walking down the aisle...Still walking. I'm about to pass the bridesmaid I hooked up with last night. Hey! I told her "Hey." And now I'm at the front with Ross. It's Phoebe. He looks pretty mad. Uh...I'd better go.
STATUS_zh: （微笑。）哦，太棒了!! （把手機放在耳邊。）你好。 （他開始護送她的過道。）不，但沒關係。她剛進來，給了他一個擁抱，那是。沒有。啊，我 - 我走了走道......仍然走路。我即將通過昨晚我聯繫的伴娘。嘿！我告訴她“嘿”。現在我在羅斯的前面。這是菲比。他看起來很瘋狂。呃......我最好去。

STATUS: I, Emily... Take thee Ross... As my lawfully wedded husband, in sickness and in health, until death parts us.
STATUS_zh: 我，艾米莉......帶著羅斯......作為我合法的丈夫，疾病和健康，直到死亡部分。

STATUS: Hey, what's up? You and me, next dance?
STATUS_zh: 嘿，怎麼了？你和我，下一個舞蹈嗎？

STATUS: Hey. I know. How could we have let this happen? Ugh! Well, y'know, we were away... I blame London.  So look umm, while we're st-still in London, I mean, we can keep doing it right? Only here. I'll meet you there in two minutes. Now? Oh, I-I don't know. Just uh, do the right thing. Toe the line. Thread the needle. Think outside the box! Wait. Rachel, no, he's married. Married! If you don't realise that, I can't help you.
STATUS_zh: 嘿。我知道。我們怎麼能讓這種情況發生？啊!好吧，你知道，我們離開了......我責怪倫敦。所以看看嗯，雖然我們是倫敦的st-仍然在倫敦，我的意思是，我們可以繼續做對嗎？只在這裡。我會在兩分鐘內見到你。現在？哦，我 - 我不知道。只是呃，做正確的事。腳趾線。擰針。創造性思考！等待。雷切爾，不，他結婚了。已婚！如果你沒有意識到，我無法幫助你。

STATUS: But my clothes are-ohh! No time for that!(They both start to frantically rip each other's clothes off, but are interrupted when Joey tries to open the door.)
STATUS_zh: 但我的衣服是 - 哦！沒有時間！（他們倆都開始瘋狂地撕掉彼此的衣服，但是當Joey試圖打開門時被打斷了。）

STATUS: Rach! Rach! Hi! What are you, what are you doing here? Oh. Not yet. Pretty soon I guess. I just, I don't understand, I mean, how-how can she do this? Y'know, what, am I, am I like a complete idiot for thinking that she'd actually show up? Same difference. I get it! Well, that's that. What? Oh, I don't, I don't, I don't know... I could, yeah, I can do that. I can't, I can't even believe her! No, y'know what, I am, I am gonna go! I know, why not? Right? Y'know-thanks! (They hug) Yeah, well...nah. Why don't you come, I mean, I-I have two tickets, why not? Yeah, yeah, it'll be great! You can, you can lay on the beach and I can cry over my failed marriage. See-see how I make jokes? No really, I mean, I mean, God, I could use a friend. Okay! Cool! Come on! Ah! Ah! I forgot my jacket!
STATUS_zh: rach！ rach！你好！你是什​​麼，你在這做什麼？哦。還沒有。很快我猜。我只是，我不明白，我的意思是，她怎麼能這樣做？ y'know，我是什麼，我，我喜歡一個完全的白痴，以便認為她真的出現了嗎？相同的差異。我知道了！好吧，就是這樣。什麼？哦，我不，我不，我不知道......我可以，是的，我可以做到這一點。我不能，我甚至不能相信她！不，你知道什麼，我，我會去！我知道，為什麼不呢？正確的？ y'know - 謝謝！ （他們擁抱）是的，嗯......你為什麼不來，我的意思是，我有兩張門票，為什麼不呢？是的，是的，它會很棒！你可以，你可以躺在海灘上，我可以哭泣婚姻失敗。看看我是如何製作笑話的？不，我的意思是，我的意思是，上帝，我可以用一個朋友。好的！涼爽的！快點！啊!啊!我忘了我的夾克！
